Commentary.Commentary: We are back for Bangladesh's reply! The players have made their way out to the middle. Shadman Islam and Mahmudul Hasan Joy to open the batting for Bangladesh. Duanne Olivier will start proceedings with the ball. Here we go...
... Second innings ...

A solid score on the board for South Africa! After being put into bat first, South Africa started on a positive note, as they went wicketless in the first session of the Test match, although it was not all pretty since then. South Africa lost wickets at regular intervals. It was the stand between Bavuma and Kyle Verreynne that took them to safer shores and remained unscathed at Stumps on Day 1. The pair though found it difficult to face the second new ball from the seamers. Wickets came in at a quick rate. Nonetheless, the tails wagged for a while and took the total to 367 runs. Bangladesh made a strong comeback in this Test match but will be very disappointed with the time they took to take the final two wickets. Khaled Ahmed though was the pick of the bowlers for Bangladesh with his four wickets, while Mehidy Hasan also made his presence felt by picking up three wickets and also showed great skills in the field throughout. Bangladesh will now hope that their opening stand gets them off to a solid start once they come out to bat after the resumption. Stay tuned to see how things pan out for the visitors!

Duanne Olivier has been adjudged LBW but this time he has sent it upstairs. This is a flatter ball, outside off and turning in sharply. Olivier stays back to defend but he misses and gets pinged on his pad. Bangladesh appeal and the umpire raises his finger after taking a lot of time. Olivier opts for a review straightaway. The Ball tracker rolls in and it suggests that the ball would have clipped the top of leg stump. It is umpire's call on wickets hitting and the on-field decision remains. South Africa are bowled out for 367.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Full, on off, defends it back to the bowler.
On off, blocked to cover.
Tossed up, around off, it turns in off the deck. Duanne Olivier tries to defend on the front foot but misses. He gets pinged on the pads. Mehidy Hasan appeals but the umpire is unmoved.
Another single now! Down leg. Simon Harmer tucks it to the leg side for one.
Loopy ball, around off, it turns in. Duanne Olivier flicks it to square leg for a quick single. Does well to pick it up off his pads.

DRINKS! What an innings this has been by the tail-enders for South Africa. Bangladesh would've loved to wrap things up pretty early on but the bowlers are being made to toil hard for the final wicket here. The amount of runs Bangladesh have leaked in search of the last two wickets has certainly shifted the momentum towards South Africa. How long will the tail wag?

Hossain hits the deck hard, around off. Simon Harmer stands tall and punches it to cover.
Swing and a miss! A length ball, outside off. Simon Harmer throws his bat at it but the ball goes past his blade.
FOUR! Top shot! Back of a length, outside off. Simon Harmer sits back and works it behind square on the off side. The ball goes a bit uppishly past the gully fielder and into the fence.
Short of a length, angling in from middle. Simon Harmer hangs back and wrists it to mid-wicket.
A bit full and around off. Simon Harmer prods and pushes it towards mid on, without much timing.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Duanne Olivier defends it out watchfully.
On leg, defended to short leg.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Duanne Olivier defends it solidly.
Floated, around off. Duanne Olivier keeps it out.
Around off, blocked out.

A loud shout for LBW but the umpire says no! Bangladesh have sent it upstairs. Wickets hitting is umpire's call and Olivier escapes! This is tossed up, around off and spinning in sharply. Dean Elgar looks to defend but he misses and gets hit on his pad. Mominul Haque opts for a review and the Ball Tracker shows that the ball would have just clipped the leg stump. The on-field decision stands.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Simon Harmer wrists it to mid-wicket, off the back foot.
This is shorter in length, around middle. Simon Harmer tucks it to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Simon Harmer defends it to the off side.
This is a length ball that jags back in a bit, from middle. Simon Harmer flicks it to deep mid-wicket and does not take the single.
Back of a length, outside off. Simon Harmer lets it through to the keeper.

This last wicket stand has been brutal to Bangladesh. The pair has stitched a 28-run stand as of now, for how long will they hurt the visitors? The mood has lightened a bit in the South African dressing room.
A full ball, outside off. Simon Harmer mistimes his drive towards the mid on fielder.
On a length, around off. Duanne Olivier keeps it out.

Full and outside off. Simon Harmer drives it wide of the deep cover fielder and rotates the strike. This is now the highest 10th wicket partnership for South Africa against Bangladesh in Test cricket.
On a length, around middle and leg. Duanne Olivier tucks it behind square on the leg side for a run.
FIVE WIDES! Bonus runs for South Africa! Ahmed bangs it into the deck, around middle. Olivier ducks underneath and the keeper fails to grab the ball as it goes over him and into the fence.
Back of a length, around middle. Duanne Olivier misses his nudge around the corner and gets hit on his thigh pad.
A length ball, outside off. Duanne Olivier lets it be.
Good-length ball, around off. Duanne Olivier defends it off the front foot.
Slower through the air, around middle. Simon Harmer pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Simon Harmer cuts it towards the cover fielder.

SIX! BANG! Enough of blocking, says Harmer! This is tossed up, on middle. Harmer gets down on his knee and slog-sweeps it way over the deep mid-wicket region for a massive biggie. 350 comes up for the Proteas!
On a length, around middle. Simon Harmer eases it to long on but does not take the single.
Shorter in length, turning in from off. Simon Harmer makes room on the off side and punches it to cover.
Tossed up, around leg, from 'round the wicket. Simon Harmer keeps it out.
Back of a length, on off. Duanne Olivier blocks it to mid on.
Fuller, on the stumps. Duanne Olivier defends it on the front foot.
Good length, outside off, left alone.
On off, blocked out.
Length ball, on off. Simon Harmer pushes it to cover for one.
Short ball, on off. Simon Harmer pulls it to deep mid-wicket.
Length ball, on off. Duanne Olivier opens the face of the blade and guides it to point.
SIX! BANG! Duanne Olivier is on a roll here. South Africa inching closer to 350 here. It is a short ball, angled down leg. Duanne Olivier swivels and smokes it over the square leg fence for a biggie.
A length ball, nips into the pads. Duanne Olivier defends it out watchfully.
Full length, outside off. Duanne Olivier smothers it to cover.
FOUR! A welcome boundary for South Africa. Ebadot Hossain serves a short ball, angled onto the body. Duanne Olivier pulls it to deep square leg for four.
Outside off, left alone by Duanne Olivier.
A maiden for Ahmed now! This is surely frustrating for Bangladesh now. A short ball, on off. Simon Harmer pulls it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, around off. Simon Harmer defends it back to the bowler.
Good length, around off. Simon Harmer eases it to mid on.
BEAUTY! A length ball, outside off, nips in a touch. Simon Harmer gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Back of a length, outside off. Simon Harmer walks across and punches it to mid off, off the bottom half.
Length ball, on off. Simon Harmer defends it to the off side.
Flighted, around middle and leg. Duanne Olivier stays back and tucks it to the leg side. Mehidy Hasan marks his seventh maiden over of this innings.
Full, on fourth stump. Duanne Olivier smothers it to point.
Full, angled into the pads. Duanne Olivier flicks it to deep short leg.
Loopy ball, outside off, turning in. Duanne Olivier defends it on the front foot.
Fuller, on off. Duanne Olivier blocks it to mid on.
On the pads, tucked to deep short leg.
A sharp bouncer, around off. Simon Harmer ducks under it without any hesitation. Duanne Olivier to face his first delivery in the next over.
Length ball, outside off. Harmer punches it to cover.
Full length, angled into the pads. Simon Harmer fails to flick it off his pads. He gets rapped. Khaled Ahmed appeals but the umpire is unmoved. No review taken though.
Jaffa this time! A length ball, around off, it nips away off the deck. Simon Harmer is drawn forward due to the length but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Slight halt in play. Khaled Ahmed seems to have hurt his right palm and the physio is out to have a check on him.
Lenght ball, on the pads. Simon Harmer tucks it to square leg for a single.
Full length, on off, driven back to the bowler.
This is floated, around middle and leg. Simon Harmer tucks it to the leg side and takes a run.
Nicely played! Full and outside off. Simon Harmer drives it through cover and collects a couple of runs.
Slower through the air, full and outside off. Simon Harmer defends it to the off side.
Tossed up, around off. Simon Harmer keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Simon Harmer cuts it through the point region and takes a couple of runs.
Around off. Blocked out.
Duanne Olivier is the last man in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another good catch from Mahmudul Hasan Joy and Khaled Ahmed gets his fourth wicket! Back of a length, around the corridor of uncertainty. Lizaad Williams stays back and has a poke at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the gully region. It is that man again, Mahmudul Hasan Joy who gets low to his right and takes a sharp catch. Much-needed breakthrough for Bangladesh!
Commentary.Howout: c Mahmudul Hasan Joy b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: Play and a miss! Full and outside off. Lizaad Williams prods to drive but it goes past his outside edge.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, angling in from outside off. Lizaad Williams hangs back to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge.

FOUR! Edgy! These are crucial runs for South Africa! Irritation for Bangladesh! Back of a length, outside off. Williams looks to push it through cover but it goes off the outer half of the blade, past the gully fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, just outside off. Lizaad Williams blocks it off the back foot.
Ahmed comes 'round the wicket and serves a length ball, around off. Lizaad Williams leans and defends it to the off side.
Looped up, around off. Simon Harmer gets forward and blocks it.
Floated, on a length, around middle. Simon Harmer stays back and tucks it with soft hands towards square leg.
Tosses it up, outside off. Simon Harmer drives it through cover for a brace.
This should take some time. Mehidy Hasan gets struck on his shin with a hard drive down the ground. The physio comes out to have a look at it.
Ouch!! That might have hurt Mehidy Hasan! Floated, full and around off. Simon Harmer pushes it back to the bowler. Hasan fails to stop it cleanly and gets hit on his left ankle.
Tossed up, around off. Simon Harmer blocks it off the front foot.
A quicker ball, full and turning in from middle. Simon Harmer prods to defend but he misses and gets hit on his pad. A stifled appeal but that was surely going down leg.
This is flatter and turning in from outside off. Lizaad Williams covers his off pole and dabs it onto the deck.
Short and outside off. Simon Harmer punches it through the cover region for a run.
FOUR! Good use of the feet! A loopy ball, around off. Simon Harmer comes down the track, takes it on the full and whacks it through the mid-wicket region for another boundary.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Simon Harmer stays back and cuts it to the point fielder.
Nicely flighted, around middle. Harmer blocks it out.
FOUR! SMASHED! A juicy full toss, around off. Simon Harmer whacks it past Ebadot Hossain at mid off for a boundary.
This is a quicker ball that goes on with the arm, from middle and leg. Lizaad Williams tickles it through fine leg for a brace.
Much slower through the air, full and around off. Lizaad Williams keeps it out.
Looped up, on a length, around off. Lizaad Williams dead-bats it.
Floated, around off. Lizaad Williams blocks it off the front foot.
Full and outside off. Simon Harmer pushes it through the off side and settles for a single.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Simon Harmer keeps it out.
We are back for the second session! The players have made their way out to the middle. Lizaad Williams and Simon Harmer to resume their innings. Mehidy Hasan will start with the ball.
... Day 2, Session 2 ...

South Africa will be keen to stretch their first innings score in the second session, while Bangladesh will look to wrap the tail up and come out to bat sooner rather than later. Do join us for another intriguing session which begins at 4.25 pm IST (10.55 am GMT).

For Bangladesh, it was Khaled Ahmed who made the second new ball talk as he struck twice in an over and set the tone for them. Just when it seemed like the partnership between Temba Bavuma and Keshav Maharaj is taking the game away from Bangladesh, Mehidy Hasan got one to spin sharply and sent back a well-set Bavuma for 93. Keshav Maharaj followed suit but the tail is wagging nicely at the moment for South Africa and Bangladesh will need to pick the remaining two wickets quickly in the post-Lunch session.

A good session for Bangladesh one will have to say, as they have managed to grab 4 wickets and conceded 81 runs in the first session of Day 2. Temba Bavuma batted really well to take South Africa to safer shores but he was denied his second Test hundred by Mehidy Hasan. South Africa though would be reasonably happy with how things went for them, having crossed the 300-run mark with two wickets still in hand.
FOUR! Lizaad Williams ends the session on a good note for South Africa. It is a low full toss, on the pads. Lizaad Williams flicks it through square leg for a boundary. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2.
Full length, on the off stump. Lizaad Williams remains solid in his defense.
Good length, on off. Williams defends it to the off side.
Full length, angled in on off. Simon Harmer flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length, on off. Harmer eases it back to the bowler.
A length ball, on off. Lizaad Williams pushes it to cover for a single.
Angled across, on off. Harmer blocks it back to the bowler.
Full, on off. Simon Harmer defends it out.
FOUR! Good stroke by Harmer! Flatter, outside off. Simon Harmer waits for it and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Looped up, around leg. Simon Harmer works it to the leg side.
Quicker, on the pads. Simon Harmer tucks it to short leg.
Fuller, on off. Simon Harmer defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, around off. Lizaad Williams keeps it out.

Lizaad Williams has been given out LBW but he has opted for a review! It is pitched outside leg and Williams survives. This is a full ball, around leg. Williams looks to play it across the line and misses. Bangladesh appeal and the umpire agrees. Williams consults with his partner and decides to send it upstairs. The Ball Tracker shows three reds at first but later, the on-field umpire realizes that the technology referred Lizaad Williams as a right-handed batter, instead of a left-hander. The Ball Tracker rolls in yet again and this time, it suggests that the ball has pitched outside leg. The on-field decision needs to be overturned!
On a length, around off. Lizaad Williams hangs back and keeps it out.
Play and a miss! A short ball, outside off. Lizaad Williams throws his bat at it but he fails to get any bat on it.
Good running between the wickets! Back of a length, around middle and leg. Simon Harmer gets on top of the bounce and dabs it onto the deck, to his left. The batters scamper for a single.
Good-length, around off. Simon Harmer blocks it off the front foot.
Nicely flighted, around off. Lizaad Williams keeps it out.
Slower through the air, around middle. Simon Harmer works it behind square on the leg side. The batters cross ends.
Tossed up delivery, around off. Lizaad Williams looks to defend off the front foot but it goes off the thick inside edge towards square leg for a single.
This is on a length, around middle and leg. Simon Harmer tucks it around the corner and takes a run.
Floated, around middle. Simon Harmer tucks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, around off and turning in late. Simon Harmer prods and wrists it past the short leg fielder.
LEG BYE! A length ball, angled down leg. Simon Harmer tries to flick it away but misses. The ball goes to square leg off his pads. They cross for a leg bye.
Length ball, on off. Harmer blocks it out watchfully.
Make that four! A length ball, outside off, it flies off the deck. Simon Harmer sways away from the line of the delivery.
Three dots on the trot! A bouncer this time, outside off. Simon Harmer lets it go to the keeper.
A length ball, on the off stump. Simon Harmer offers full face of the blade.
Full length, angled into off. Simon Harmer defends it to mid off.
Tossed up, on off. Lizaad Williams blocks it out watchfully.
On off, blocked out.
Full, angled into off. Lizaad Williams defends it into the deck.
Flatter, around off. Lizaad Williams bunts it down to the off side.
Looped up, around off. Lizaad Williams defends it to the left of silly point.
Floated, full and outside off. Lizaad Williams defends it to cover.
LEG BYE! Full length, on the pads. Lizaad Williams misses his flick. The ball rolls out off the pads. The batters cross for a leg bye. Lizaad Williams yet to get off the mark in Test cricket.
Much quicker this time. Fuller, on off. Lizaad Williams defends it awkwardly to cover.
A yorker length delivery, on the fourth stump. Lizaad Williams blocks it out watchfully.
Good length, outside off. Lizaad Williams punches it to point.
Full length, outside off. Lizaad Williams blocks it to cover on the front foot.
Lizaad Williams is the new batter in.

OUT! CLEANED UP! Ebadot Hossain picks up second wicket of the innings. Bangla Tigers are roaring loud here. It is a full-length ball, on the off stump, tailing in a bit. Keshav Maharaj stays back, tries to dig it out but misses. The ball sneaks through to rattle the stumps. There comes the salute from Ebadot!  Bangladesh want to end things quickly now. Can they force an early lunch here, after it being extended by 15 minutes than usual time?
Commentary.Howout: b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary.Commentary: Simon Harmer walks out to bat.

OUT! TIMBER! The wait continues for Temba Bavuma to get his second Test century. A splendid innings comes to an end. We can see some disappointed faces in the pavilion but eventually they rise to applaud this incredible innings from Bavuma. Coming to the delivery - Mehidy Hasan serves a floated delivery, around off. It turns in a long way off the deck. Temba Bavuma goes back and tries to cut it away but misses. The ball hits him on the pads and goes on to crash into the stumps.
Commentary.Howout: b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Full length, on middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj comes down the track and whips it to deep square leg. It meets the fielder on a bounce.
Fuller, on off. Maharaj defends it to point off the outer half.

FOUR! Nicely played! What a handy knock Keshav Maharaj is playing here. It is looped up, turning down leg. Keshav Maharaj glances it around the corner and bags a boundary. The stand moves to 50 as well.
Flatter, on the pads. Temba Bavuma tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single. Bavuma moves to 93.
Fuller, outside off. Temba Bavuma defends it on the front foot.
Length ball, on off. Keshav Maharaj defends the only ball that he had to face.
Full length, around off. Temba Bavuma drives it to cover for a single.
Good length, outside off. Temba Bavuma lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball, on off. Bavuma defends it to the off side.
Another one outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length, wide of off. Temba Bavuma ignores his temptation and keeps the bat back.
This is darted on the pads. Temba Bavuma tucks it to the leg side for a single. He will retain the strike.
Floated, on a length, around off and spinning in late. Temba Bavuma skips down the track and looks to heave it away but he misses and gets hit on his body. Sharp turn there for Mehidy Hasan!
Flatter ball, around middle. Temba Bavuma wrists it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, around off. Temba Bavuma blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Nicely done! Tossed up, around leg. Temba Bavuma kneels and paddles it through the fine leg region for a boundary. Bavuma moves into the 90s.
Tosses it up, on the pads. Temba Bavuma tucks it to mid-wicket.

Back of a length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj looks to block but the ball takes off from a length and hits the splice of Maharaj's bat. The ball lobs up but lands safely in front of the extra cover fielder.
Ahmed goes back over the wicket and hurls a length ball, around off. Keshav Maharaj keeps it out.
FOUR! Nicely done! A bumper, angling across the batter. Keshav Maharaj hops in his crease and cuts it way over the gully region. Two bounces and over the ropes.
No ball! A short ball, around off. Keshav Maharaj ducks underneath. Khaled Ahmed oversteps and the umpire signals no ball.

FOUR! WHACKED! Change of angle doesn't work for Ahmed! He comes 'round the wicket and serves a full ball, outside off. Keshav Maharaj prods and caresses it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Ahmed bangs it into the deck, outside off. Keshav Maharaj hangs back and lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Bavuma slaps it without much timing through the point region for a single.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Hossain goes full and around off. Keshav Maharaj covers his off pole and blocks it.
Back of a length, just outside off. Maharaj keeps it out watchfully.
Short of a length, around off. Bavuma gets behind the line of the ball and defends it to the off side. The batters cross ends.
A full ball, well outside off. Temba Bavuma reaches out and carves it through the cover region. The fielder in the deep runs across to his right and cuts it off. Two runs taken.
Good-length ball, shaping in from off. Maharaj looks to block off the back foot. It goes off the thick inside edge towards mid-wicket for a single.
This a full ball, well outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Another ball that nips back in late from outside off. Bavuma tries to keep it out but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
A bit full, around off. Bavuma defends it to the off side and looks for a run but is sent back by Maharaj.
On a good length, outside off. Temba Bavuma lets it be.
FOUR! Ahmed overcooks it, around middle. Bavuma flicks it nonchalantly through the mid-wicket region. The ball races away to the fence. Top shot from Bavuma!

A huge appeal for LBW but the umpire shakes his head! This is a good-length ball, just outside off and nipping back in sharply. Bavuma looks to defend off the front foot but he misses and gets hit high on his pad. Height might have been the issue here.
Hossain goes full this time, around off. Keshav Maharaj prods and defends it to the off side.
Slightly short and on off. Maharaj hangs back and taps it towards backward point.
A length ball, angling down leg. Keshav Maharaj gets inside the line of the ball and lets it be.
On a length, around off. Keshav Maharaj keeps it out.

DROPPED! That ball took off from a length but the fielder didn't manage to hold onto it. Short of a length, around off. Some extra bounce on offer for Hossain. Bavuma feels for it. The ball goes off the splice of his bat and flies to the right of the second slip fielder. Yasir Ali there, dives to his right, gets a hand to it but puts it down. The ball rolls towards third man for a run. Will this prove to be costly for Bangladesh?
A full ball, well outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Back of a length, angling in from middle. Bavuma stays back and tucks it around the corner for a single.
This is a full ball, jags back in late from outside off. Bavuma watches it sail through to the keeper.
On a length, outside off. Bavuma lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Shot of authority from Bavuma! Taskin hurls a full ball, on middle and leg. Bavuma leans and whips it through the mid-wicket region for a cracking boundary.
Good-length delivery, jagging back in from off. Bavuma gets forward and defends it solidly, back to the bowler.
A full ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma mistimes his drive towards mid off.

DRINKS! Bangladesh has certainly made the second new ball talk and the first hour of Day 2 belongs to them! They have been much better with their lines and lengths this time around and they will look to take the remaining wickets without conceding too many runs. The Proteas would hope that Temba Bavuma bats deep, along with their tail and takes them to a good first innings total.
Back of a length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj taps it to point.
Outside off, left alone by Maharaj.
FOUR BYES! A full-length ball, angling down leg. It nips further away from Liton Das' reach and races away to the fine leg fence.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, wide of off. Keshav Maharaj slashes at it but misses.
Full length, outside off, it flies off the deck. Keshav Maharaj does not get enticed this time and makes a nice leave.
Short ball, on off. Maharaj hops and blocks it to the off side.
Full length, angled into off. Temba Bavuma defends it out on the front foot.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
Outside off, left alone by Temba Bavuma.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Temba Bavuma ducks under it.

Length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Back of a length, wide of off. Keshav Maharaj dashes hard at it but only connects with thin air.
A length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Keshav Maharaj tries to punch it to the off side but misses.
Back of a length, on the bodyline. Keshav Maharaj tries to duck under it but in the end takes a blow on his left palm. He soon comes down the track to fist bump his partner. He looks to be fine.
A quick single now as this length delivery is tucked to short mid-wicket.
Quicker now. Good length, outside off, some extra bounce off the deck. Temba Bavuma looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
Ebadot Hossain comes into the attack now. Will he strike straightaway?
Khaled Ahmed serves a short ball, around leg, bowling to his field this time. Keshav Maharaj anticipates the short one and ducks under it with ease.
A length ball, on leg. Temba Bavuma tucks it to mid-wicket for a single.
A sharp bouncer, around off. Temba Bavuma ducks under it with ease.
A length ball, on the pads. Keshav Maharaj flicks it to deep square leg for a single.

What a delivery! Good length, outside off, shaping away off the deck. Keshav Maharaj tries to play it away from his body but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Touch short, outside off, it nips in a touch off the deck. Temba Bavuma shoulders his arms at it.
Outside off, left alone.
Full length, on the stumps. Bavuma defends it to cover.
This one pitches wide outside off and shapes away as well off the deck. Temba Bavuma has no trouble with it.
On a length, outside off, gets some extra bounce as well. Temba Bavuma continues to leave the ball away from his body.
Full length, angled into off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out solidly.
Back of a length, around off. Keshav Maharaj covers his off pole and defends it with ease.

BEATEN! A loud shout for caught behind but the umpire is not interested! Excellent delivery from Ahmed! He is in the middle of a really good spell here! This one comes in with the angle from outside off, on a length and straightens a bit after landing. Keshav Maharaj looks to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Pitches it up, just outside off. Keshav Maharaj does not bother playing at that one.
Good-length delivery, coming in with the angle from middle. Bavuma nudges it wide of the mid-wicket fielder for a single.
Corrects his line and hurls a length ball, around off. Bavuma gets on top of the bounce and dabs it onto the deck.
On a length and well outside off. Bavuma leaves it alone.
This is a good-length ball, around off. Keshav Maharaj blocks it out.
Short of a length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj lets it through to the keeper.
Around middle. Temba Bavuma tucks it around the corner for a single.

An appeal for LBW but the umpire says no! Bangladesh have opted for a review! Umpire's call on wickets hitting and Temba Bavuma survives! Top delivery from Taskin! Good-length ball, jagging back in late from outside off. Bavuma looks to defend but he misses and gets hit high on his pad. Bangladesh appeal but the umpire doesn't agree. They send it upstairs. The Ball Tracker shows that the ball would have just clipped the leg stump. The on-field decision stays.
Back of a length, angling in from middle. Temba Bavuma keeps it out.
A full ball, around off. Temba Bavuma digs it out towards mid off.
Back of a length, around off. Keshav Maharaj stays back and defends it. A double-wicket maiden from Khaled Ahmed! Sensational bowling.
A length ball, on the leg stump. Keshav Maharaj flicks it to the leg side.
Khaled Ahmed misses out on his maiden Test Hat-Trick. But boy, he has got his side back into the game. Good length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj leaves it alone for the keeper.
Keshav Maharaj is the new batter in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Two in two for Khaled Ahmed and he is on a roll! This is exactly the kind of start that Bangladesh would have hoped for going into Day 2! Wiaan Mulder departs for a golden duck! Ahmed is on a hat-trick. Coming to the delivery - This is a length ball, around the corridor of uncertainty. Wiaan Mulder feels for it. It takes the thick outside edge and goes to the left of the gully fielder. Mahmudul Hasan Joy there, moves quickly to his left and gets low to take a really good catch. Terrific passage of play for the Bangla Tigers.
Commentary.Howout: c Mahmudul Hasan Joy b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: Wiaan Mulder comes in at number 7.

Kyle Verreynne takes the review straightaway for being adjudged lbw! That looked plumb in front! Khaled Ahmed strikes and the second new ball seems to be doing the trick for the tourists. Lovely bowling from Khaled Ahmed! Another ball that stayed a touch low. A length delivery, landing just outside off and nipping back in sharply. Kyle hangs back to keep it out but he misses and gets pinged on his front pad. Bangladesh appeal and the umpire agrees. Kyle though opts for a review after consulting with Bavuma. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows three reds. The umpire raises his finger yet again. Kyle is a goner and South Africa lose a review as well.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: BEATEN! A length ball, just outside off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and looks to push it through the off side. The ball stays a bit low and sneaks through his bat.
On a length, just outside off. Kyle pushes it wide of the mid off fielder, without any feet movement. The batters take a run. Kyle will retain the strike.
Much better line and length from Taskin! This one lands around the fourth stump channel and jags away just that little bit. Kyle prods and defends it solidly.
On a length and outside off. Kyle Verreynne has no shot to offer.
Good-length ball, shaping away from outside off. Kyle lets it through to the keeper.
Another delivery that is full and outside off. Kyle leans and drives but finds the fielder at short extra cover who half-stops it.
Taskin serves a fuller-length ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne reaches out and pushes it to cover.
Will we see pace from the other end as well? Yes, we will. Taskin Ahmed comes into the attack now.
Ahmed drags his length back, just outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
FOUR! Not from the middle of the bat but Bavuma will take that! A very full ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma reaches out and whacks it through the cover region for a boundary.
This is a length ball, jagging back in late from off. Bavuma stands tall and tucks it to square leg.
On a length and way outside off. Bavuma covers his off pole and shoulders his arms at this one.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
FOUR! Ahmed errs in line and serves it around the pads. Bavuma just helps it on its way through the fine leg region for a boundary.
The second new ball is now due. Will Bangladesh opt for it straightaway? Yes, they do.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne works it to the leg side.
Darted on the pads, Kyle Verreynne clips it to the leg side.
On off, defended back to the bowler.
Short and on middle. Kyle Verreynne uses the depth of the crease, flicks it to mid-wicket and yells 'NO' straightaway for a single.
Quicker, fuller and on off. Kyle Verreynne defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller, around leg. Kyle Verreynne eases it to mid on.
Full length, on the fourth stump. Temba Bavuma defends on the front foot.
Good length, on the pads. Temba Bavuma flicks it through square leg for a brace.
On a length, on off. This one hurries onto the batter. Temba Bavuma stays inside the crease to greet it with full face of the blade.
Length ball, on off, blocked out.
Back of a length, around off. Temba Bavuma stays back and blocks it out.
Full length, outside off. Temba Bavuma defends it to cover.
A dot to end the over! Darted on the pads. Kyle Verreynne goes deep inside the crease and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tosses it up, full and on leg. Kyle Verreynne flicks it to the leg side.
So, Bavuma gets the first run of the day. It is full, on the pads. Temba Bavuma tucks it to square leg for a single.
Full and on the stumps. Bavuma clips it to the leg side.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Temba Bavuma flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Flighted, full and outside off. Bavuma defends it on the front foot.
It will be Mehidy Hasan to turn the ball from the other end.
Full length, on the fifth stump line. Kyle Verreynne shoulders his arms at it.

The morning session on Day 2 is set to begin. The Bangladesh players stride out to the middle. Followed by Kyle Verreynne and Temba Bavuma who walk out with their swords. Khaled Ahmed to continue his unfinished over. Here we go...

Mehidy Hasan is up for a quick chat. He says that it is difficult to keep your concentration in Test cricket but he is always anticipating that the ball is coming towards him. Tells that he likes to take good catches and tries to cash in on any opportunity that comes his way. Mentions that while bowling he is always looking for dot balls.

Early stumps have been an issue in Durban for a long time. Knowing that the bad light situation arises every time we play Test cricket in Durban, why does it not make sense to play pink-ball Test at this venue? At least we will be entertained with a good game of cricket.

After seeing the action on Day 1, the question of some major players missing should not arise anymore. Even without the big names, the first three sessions of this Test match couldn’t have been any better. Bangladesh would be a tad disappointed with how the day ended. Nonetheless, their bowlers outclassed the South African batting lineup in the afternoon session and would hope to repeat the same in the morning session of Day 2. For the hosts, the fifth-wicket stand holds the key. Will they be able to cross the 300-run mark? Stay tuned to find how things pan out.

The sun is out and shining in Durban, although you never know when the umpire might just call it a day. It is now time for Day 2 of the first Test between South Africa and Bangladesh. The visitors would want to do the talking with the new ball which will soon be available. On that note, welcome to our coverage.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

Bangladesh did really well to make inroads in the second session. Although, the stand between Bavuma-Verreynne has started to bother them. Bangladesh would be desperate to break this stand as soon as possible. Their bowlers would be itching to come back on the field, keeping in mind the new ball is due in 3.1 overs. It will surely be an exciting day of cricket. As of now, South Africa would be the happier of the two sides whereas Bangladesh would be looking to come back stronger on Day 2. The action on Day 2 will begin at 1.30 pm IST (8 am GMT). But our build-up will begin much earlier. Do join us for the same. Till then, cheers and goodbye!

Woah! Day 1 ends pretty abruptly. A surprise for everyone, to be honest, but not for the umpires it seems. Coming back to the game - Well, that was some recovery by Temba Bavuma and Kyle Verreynne. Both the batters took their time, but once they got their eye in, there was no stopping the two. South Africa lost a sole wicket in the final session of Ryan Rickelton before the umpires called off the proceedings on Day 1. Although, the debutant looked really good at the crease and with time should only improve. The fifth-wicket stand is of 53 runs which remains unbeaten. South Africa would hope these two batters will bat deep on Day 2 and continue from where they left off.

OH DEAR! The umpires converge to have a word and within a second, they have concluded that the Day 1 comes to an end due to Bad light! The sun has still not set yet, also the artificial lights were on, but even that could not help the umpires to change their decision.
Full length, on the stumps. Kyle Verreynne defends it to mid on.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire is not interested! This one nips back in sharply from outside off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back to defend but he misses and gets hit high on his pad.
Ahmed serves it on a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma punches it through the cover region and settles for a run.
A bumper, around middle. Bavuma ducks underneath.
Pitches it up, just outside off. Kyle Verreynne pushes it wide of the mid off fielder and rotates the strike.
Change. Khaled Ahmed comes back into the attack now.
This is a flighted delivery, around off. Temba Bavuma keeps it out.
Full and outside off. Temba Bavuma hangs back and punches it a bit uppishly towards the mid off fielder.
Tossed up delivery, around off. Temba Bavuma keeps it out.
Hasan serves a quicker ball, around middle. Bavuma sits back and nudges it to mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, turning in from middle. Temba Bavuma tucks it to the leg side.
Tossed up, around off. Temba Bavuma blocks it off the front foot.
Taskin goes 'round the wicket and serves a short-of-a-length ball, around off. Bavuma taps it towards point and takes a single.
Another ball, short and around middle. Temba Bavuma gets down in time and lets it through to the keeper.
A bumper, angling down leg. Temba Bavuma ducks underneath.
A short ball, around middle. Kyle Verreynne pulls it without much timing behind square on the leg side. The batters cross ends. That also brings up the 50-run stand between these two!
Shorter in length, angling in from off. Kyle Verreynne gets on top of the bounce and defends it onto the deck.
Back of a length, well outside off. Kyle Verreynne lets it be.
Tosses it up, around off. Temba Bavuma defends it out watchfully.
Floated, on a length, around off. Temba Bavuma blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on middle. Temba Bavuma nudges it to the leg side.
Kyle comes down the track and eases it towards long on for a run.
This is a quicker ball, on a length, around middle. Kyle Verreynne sits back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full and on middle. Bavuma pushes it to mid on for a quick single.
Fuller, angled down leg. Kyle Verreynne flicks it to deep square leg off his pads. The batters take two runs.

What a brilliant knock by Temba Bavuma. He gets to his FIFTY with this single. A length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma punches it through point for a quick single. This is his 18th Test fifty. Can he convert it into three digits?
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Temba Bavuma sways away from the line of the delivery.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single. The ball does not carry to the man stationed there.
Good length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne walks across and leaves it alone.
A single now, as this is pushed to mid off. Temba Bavuma choosing the right fielders here to take on.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Temba Bavuma works it to long on for a single.
Flatter and outside off. Kyle Verreynne taps it to point for one.

Around middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne pushes it to the right of the bowler. Hasan dives to that side and makes a half-stop. Saves a single this time. Mehidy Hasan fields really well off his own bowling.
Flighted, full, around middle. Kyle Verreynne works it to the right of the bowler. Mehidy Hasan sprints that side and keeps it in control.
Full, on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller, angled down leg. Kyle Verreynne clears his front leg and defends it to mid-wicket.
Two dots on the trot to end the over. On a length, around off. Temba Bavuma defends it with full face, back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Temba Bavuma.

FOUR! This should release some pressure, no matter how the runs came. Slightly short, outside off. Temba Bavuma slashes hard at it. The ball takes the under-edge, sneaks through the slip cordon and races away to the boundary at third man.
An effort delivery, outside off. Temba Bavuma has no stroke to offer.
Full length, on the pads. Temba Bavuma eases it to mid on.
Full, outside off, Bavuma defends it to point.
Angled in, full and on off. Kyle Verreynne defends it back to the bowler.
Full, on off, blocked out watchfully.
Loopy ball, around off, turns in off the deck. Kyle Verreynne goes back and defends it to square leg.
Full, on the pads. Kyle Verreynne flicks it to the leg side.
On the stumps. Kyle Verreynne blocks it out solidly.

Tossed up, around middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne tries to chase it but misses. Liton Das moves to his left and gathers the ball. Most of the Bangladesh players around the batter put in an appeal, but the umpire shows no interest.
Back of a length, outside off. It nips in a touch off the deck. Temba Bavuma stays inside the crease, shoulders his arms at it. The ball misses his pads by a whisker.
Full length, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
FOUR! Nicely played. Short ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma punches it through covers. The ball races away to the fence. He moves into his 40s now.
Length, on off, blocked out.
Full length, outside off. Temba Bavuma drives it crisply to covers but straight to the fielder.
Full length, on off stump. Temba Bavuma drives it to the left of mid on. Could not clear the man though.
Ahmed hits the deck hard, just outside off. Kyle Verreynne defends it solidly.
A bit full, around middle. Kyle Verreynne pushes it towards the mid on fielder.
Short of a length, around middle. Kyle Verreynne gets behind the line of the ball and keeps it out.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! A length ball, darted on the pads. Kyle Verreynne tickles it through the fine leg region. Ebadot Hossain there, makes a mess of it near the boundary ropes and the ball goes past the ropes.
On a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne stands tall and pushes it to the mid off fielder.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and punches it through the cover region for a boundary.
Shorter in length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne sits back and cuts it through the point region for a single.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Kyle Verreynne rocks back and manages it towards the point fielder quite awkwardly.

Oh dear, Temba Bavuma has taken a blow here. He is on the ground with some issue with his left wrist, as he tried to dodge the throw from the deep. The physio runs in to have a check on Temba Bavuma. As he is getting nursed, the umpires decide to call for a DRINKS break. South Africa started the final session really well, but Ryan Rickelton could not stick around for long. Temba Bavuma is still at the crease and he holds the key for his side in this innings now, hope he hasn't injured himself. Bangladesh know a wicket or two will get the tail in. An enticing passage of play awaits, Do not go anywhere.
In the air....but safe! A short ball, around off. Temba Bavuma pulls it without much timing towards deep mid-wicket. The ball falls just short of the deep mid-wicket fielder. A single taken.
Floated, around off. Bavuma blocks it off the front foot.
On a length, around off. Bavuma keeps it out.
A short ball, around middle. Temba Bavuma rocks back and mistimes his pull shot towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Ahmed hits the deck hard, just outside off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and pushes it to cover.

FOUR! STREAKY! Shorter in length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne hangs back and looks to push it through the off side. The ball goes off the outside edge through the gap between second slip and gully and races away to the fence. 200 comes up for South Africa as well!
On a length and around off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it off the front foot.
Good-length ball, just outside off. Kyle Verreynne sits back and pushes it to extra cover.
Short of a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne dabs it towards backward point.
Play and a miss! Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne throws his bat at it but the ball zips past his blade.
On a length, around off. Temba Bavuma keeps it out.
Slightly short and around off. Kyle Verreynne cuts it through poit and collects a run.
A loopy ball, on a length, around leg. Kyle Verreynne prods to defend but he misses and gets hit low on his pad.
A quicker ball, coming in with the angle from off. Kyle Verreynne manages to dab it towards point in the end.
This is full and well outside off. Temba Bavuma reaches out and carves it wide of the sweeper cover for a single.
Flatter ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma stays back and pushes it towards cover.
A full ball, around leg. Kyle Verreynne flicks it in front of square on the leg side for a brace.
A full ball, around middle. Kyle Verreynne flicks but the fielder at mid-wicket dives to his left and saves at least a couple of runs for his side.
Good-length ball, just outside off. Kyle Verreynne gets forward and pushes it to cover.
On a good length, around off. Kyle Verreynne looks to defend by staying back but he gets squared up. The ball goes off the thick outside edge towards the backward point fielder.
A bit full, outside off. Kyle Verreynne prods to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
Back of a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and blocks it.
Fuller, outside off. Bavuma blocks it to cover.
On off, pushed to cover for a single.

A risky run but no danger in the end! Darted on the pads. Temba Bavuma flicks it to mid-wicket for a quick single. Temba Bavuma hesitated a bit as he was charging towards the other end, but the throw went in the other direction.
Around middle and leg. Kyle Verreynne flicks it to mid-wicket for one.
Full, outside off, pushed to cover.
Short ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma cuts it to sweeper cover for a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length, on the fourth stump line. Kyle Verreynne steps across and blocks it to cover with hard hands.
Good length, outside off, skidding through. Kyle Verreynne shoulders his arms at it.
Touch short, around the hips. Kyle Verreynne hops inside the crease and tucks it to the leg side.
Length ball, on the pads. Temba Bavuma clips it to square leg for one.
Full length, angled into off. Temba Bavuma stays back and blocks it out with ease.
Just 2 runs off it then! Bangladesh continue to stem the run flow. This one is sliding down the leg side. Kyle Verreynne stays back but fails to clip it away.
Full and on middle. Temba Bavuma clips it to mid on for a quick single.
Angled into the pads, Temba Bavuma eases it to short mid-wicket.
Outside off, Bavuma defends it to cover on the front foot.
Floated, full and outside off. Temba Bavuma prods and blocks it into the deck.
Length ball, on the pads. Kyle Verreynne tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
Play and a miss!  A beauty to end the over with. On a fuller side, aimed at the fourth stump line. Bavuma tries to drive it away but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length, Kyle Verreynne pulls it to mid-wicket. The fielder there makes a half stop. The batters take a quick single.
Full length, around middle. Kyle Verreynne drives it to mid on.
Good length, angled into the pads. Kyle Verreynne flicks it square on the leg side.
A length ball, on the stumps. Temba Bavuma works it to fine leg off a thick inside edge. The batters cross for a single.
Fuller, on off. Kyle Verreynne goes back to defend it out. Just a single off the over.
Around off, blocked out solidly.
Looped up, full and on the stumps. Kyle Verreynne prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Full, on middle and leg. Bavuma drives it down the ground to long on for a single.
On off, flicked to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Top shot! Floated, full and outside off. Temba Bavuma leans in and creams it through the cover region for a boundary.
A length ball, well outside off. Kyle Verreynne lets it through to the keeper. A wicket-maiden from Ebadot Hossain!
On a length, around off. Kyle Verreynne defends it solidly off the front foot.
This is full and outside off. Kyle Verreynne prods and carves it to the point fielder, along the ground.
Good-length ball, around middle. Kyle Verreynne stays back and blocks it.
Kyle Verreynne is the new batter in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ebadot Hossain strikes now and it is the debutant, Ryan Rickelton who takes the walk back to the pavilion! Hossain bangs it into the deck, around off. Ryan sits back and looks to pull. The ball hurries onto him and he gets cramped for room. It takes the toe end of the bat and the ball goes in the air towards mid on. The skipper of Bangladesh, Mominul Haque settles under it and takes a sitter. South Africa lose their fourth wicket now.
Commentary.Howout: c Mominul Haque b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary.Commentary: BEATEN! This is a length ball, around middle that jags back in sharply. Ryan Rickelton gets across to block but the ball sneaks through the gap between his bat and pad. Liton Das behind the sticks dives to his right but fails to grab it cleanly.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Temba Bavuma rocks back and punches it to cover.
Nicely flighted, around off. Temba Bavuma keeps it out watchfully.
Tosses it up, on middle and turning down leg. Temba Bavuma misses his nudge around the corner.
Full and just outside off. Ryan Rickelton clears his front leg and works it wide of the mid off fielder for a single.
Floated, full and around off. Ryan Rickelton defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up, on off. Ryan Rickelton dead-bats it.
A length ball, just outside off. Ryan Rickelton defends it towards point and takes a quick single. He will retain the strike.
Back of a length, on off. Ryan Rickelton hangs back and blocks it off the back foot.
Pitched up, around middle. Ryan Rickelton leans and pushes it towards mid on.
On a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton covers his off pole and defends it.
Short of a length, on middle. Ryan tucks it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! STREAKY! A full ball, way outside off. Ryan Rickelton looks for a booming drive but it goes off the thick outside edge past the gully fielder for a boundary.
An overpitched ball, around off. Temba Bavuma leans and tucks it to mid-wicket.
This is a flatter ball, around middle and leg. Temba Bavuma rocks back and nudges it towards square leg.
Full and around middle. Temba Bavuma wrists it to mid-wicket.
Around off. Temba Bavuma covers the line and blocks it.
Floated, on middle. Temba Bavuma gets forward and keeps it out.
Tossed up, around leg. Temba Bavuma glances it through fine leg for a brace.

An appeal for LBW but the umpire says no! Bangladesh have opted for a review though! A length ball, around leg. Ryan Rickelton misses his flick and gets hit on his pad. Ebadot Hossain appeals but it is turned down! The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the ball was pitched way outside leg. Ryan survives. Bangladesh burn another review. The on-field decision remains.
Pitches it up, just outside off. Ryan Rickelton prods and lets it be.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Width on offer, outside off. Ryan Rickelton sits back and slaps it through the cover region for a cracking boundary.
Back of a length, angling across the batter. Ryan Rickelton covers his off stump and leaves it alone.
Another ball, full and outside off. Temba Bavuma drives it through the cover region and collects three runs. The fielder at cover gives it a chase and cuts it off.
Hossain starts with a full ball, around off. Temba Bavuma keeps it out, off the front foot.

We are back for the last session of Day 1! The players have made their way out to the middle. Ryan Rickelton and Temba Bavuma will resume their innings. Ebadot Hossain will start with the ball. Let's go...
... Day 1, Session 3 ...

Bangladesh started the post-Lunch session by putting the right foot forward. The bowlers bowled much better lines and lengths, which resulted in two key wickets, as they saw the back of both the South African openers. Bangladesh looked really sharp in the field as well, they did not let Elgar and Erwee find the gaps easily as they did in the morning session. The stand between Keegan Petersen and Bavuma started to hurt them a bit. But an inspirational moment in the field by Mehidy Hasan made sure to send back Keegan Petersen on a timid score. The momentum is surely with the visiting side going into the break. Can they capitalize on it in the final session? To find out, do join us 1900 IST (1330 GMT).

This could’ve been a session of two halves, but the stunning arm of Mehidy Hasan made sure that the afternoon session belonged to the visitors. So, we saw 28 overs being bowled, where the Proteas scored 70 runs but also lost three wickets. A brilliant comeback made by Bangladesh in this match.
Tosses it up, around off. Ryan Rickelton dabs it onto the deck, off the front foot. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1!
Looped up, on a length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton gets forward but does not offer any shot to it.
This is a flatter ball, going on with the arm, from middle. Ryan Rickelton hangs back and defends it onto the deck.
Shorter in length, spinning in from middle. Bavuma sits back and flicks it to deep square leg for a run.
Flighted ball, on middle. Temba Bavuma prods and works it to mid on.
Flatter and quicker, around leg. Bavuma rocks back and tickles it towards short fine leg.
Play and a miss! Back of a length, shaping away from well outside off. Ryan Rickelton throws his bat at it but the ball goes past his blade towards the keeper.
Shorter in length, around middle and leg. Ryan Rickelton hangs back and wrists it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, shaping away from outside off. Ryan Rickelton shoulders his arms to this one.
A full ball, angling across the batter. Ryan Rickelton leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around middle. Ryan Rickelton stays back and dabs it onto the deck.
Good-length ball, around off. Ryan Rickelton prods to defend it.

FOUR! Lovely timing and even better placement from Bavuma! This is an overpitched ball, around middle. Bavuma clears his front leg and whips it through the mid-wicket region. The ball races away to the fence. There were two fielders there but Bavuma pierced the gap to perfection!
Floated, around leg. Temba Bavuma looks to sweep but he misses and gets hit on the pad, outside the line.
A quicker ball, on a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton looks to block but it goes off the thick inside edge towards square leg for a single.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Ryan Rickelton rocks back and punches it towards mid off.
Tosses it up, spinning away from outside off. Ryan Rickelton covers his off stump and lets it through to the keeper.
Floated, outside off. Ryan Rickelton lets it be.
A length ball, angling in from 'round the wicket. Ryan Rickelton prods to defend but he gets an inside edge onto his pad. The ball lobs up in the vacant square leg region. A single taken!
Taskin changes his angle and comes 'round the wicket. He serves a good-length ball, outside off. Ryan shoulders his arms at it by covering his off pole.
Back of a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton gets on top of the bounce and defends it.
FOUR! CLASSY! An overpitched ball, just outside off. Ryan Rickelton prods and creams it through the vacant mid off region for a boundary. Excellent batting!
A full ball, on middle. Ryan Rickelton leans and works it towards the mid off fielder.
On a length and angling across the batter. Ryan Rickelton prods and shoulders his arms at it.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Bavuma dead-bats it.
Floated, on a length, around middle, from 'round the wicket. Bavuma blocks it off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Temba Bavuma gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it.
Flatter and quicker, around leg. Ryan Rickelton tucks it around the corner and takes a single.
FOUR! That is some way to open your account in Test cricket! Tossed up, on middle. Ryan Rickelton kneels and reverse-sweeps it past the backward point fielder for a boundary.
Floated, around off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out.

An appeal for caught behind but nothing from the umpire. Short of a length, taking off from a length, around the fifth stump channel. Bavuma feels for it but the ball zips past his outside edge. Excellent delivery from Taskin!
Nicely played! Full and outside off. Temba Bavuma drives it through cover and takes a couple of runs.
This lands on a good length, just outside off. Temba Bavuma prods and defends it towards point.
On a length and jagging back in from outside off. Bavuma lets it be.
Short of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma stays back and punches it to the cover fielder.
Full and outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone.
Full, angled into the pads. Ryan Rickelton tucks it to the leg side.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up, on the stumps. Ryan Rickelton defends it on the front foot.
Looped up, full and on off. Ryan Rickelton blocks it back to the bowler.
Full and on the stumps. Temba Bavuma pushes it to extra cover for a quick single.
Full, outside off. Temba Bavuma blocks it back to the bowler.
Ryan Rickelton is the new man in.

OUT! RUN OUT! Mehidy Hasan, you beauty! Huge moment in this game and it is Mehidy Hasan's brilliance in the field that sees the back of Keegan Petersen. Much-needed breakthrough for Bangladesh as Bavuma and Petersen were looking to take the game away from the tourists. This was a full ball, outside off. Bavuma prods and slices it towards the point region. Mehidy Hasan at backward point, moves across to his right, puts in a dive and stops it one-handed. He then gets up quickly, throws it to the striker's end and scores a direct hit. Keegan Petersen is well short of his crease as he looks to steal a run. Petersen stands there in disbelief. Absolutely brilliant from Mehidy Hasan!
Commentary.Howout: run out (Mehidy Hasan)

Commentary.Commentary: Is that a run out? The umpire takes it upstairs to confirm. The replays late roll in to confirm that Keegan Petersen is well short of the crease.
Fuller in length, outside off. Temba Bavuma does not have any to offer.
This is a length ball, angling in just that little bit from outside off. Temba Bavuma covers his off pole and keeps it out.
Short of a length, around the fifth stump channel. Temba Bavuma lets it through to the keeper.
Pitches it up, outside off. Temba Bavuma looks to drive it through cover but it goes off the inner half towards mid on.
Good-length ball, around off. Temba Bavuma prods and defends it solidly towards cover.
Tossed up, full, on off. Keegan Petersen drives it aerially to the left of the bowler. Mehidy Hasan dives to that side to make a half-stop.
Full, on sixth stump, angled across. Keegan Petersen gets behind the line to block it out.
On off, blocked back to the bowler.
Quicker. Full and outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Short ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen goes back and cuts it to point.
Tossed up, on off. Keegan Petersen defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off, nips in late off the deck. Temba Bavuma has no stroke to offer.
Good length, outside off. Temba Bavuma prods and shoulders his arms.
Length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma opens the face and steers it towards gully. The fielder there dives to his right to make a sharp stop.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
FOUR! EDGY! Temba Bavuma rides his luck now. Full length, outside off. Temba Bavuma tries to drive it away. The ball takes the outside edge and goes through the gap at slip cordon for a boundary.
Fuller, outside off. Keegan Petersen steps across and pushes it to cover for a run.
Darted on the pads. Temba Bavuma tucks it to the leg side.
Tossed up, on the stumps. Temba Bavuma blocks it to the right of the bowler.
Fuller, outside off. Temba Bavuma pushes it to cover on the front foot.
On middle and leg, blocked back to the bowler.
Flighted, full and on off. Temba Bavuma defends it to the leg side yet again.
Fuller, on middle. Temba Bavuma eases it to the leg side.
On a length, well outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone. A maiden over from Taskin Ahmed!
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen lets it be.

An appeal for caught behind but the umpire is not interested! This is a full ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen looks to drive away from his body. Doesn't get to the pitch of the ball and the ball goes past his outside edge. There was certainly some noise as the ball passed the bat but Bangladesh don't opt for a review. Oh, dear! The replays show that there was a deflection on the UltraEdge and had Mominul Haque opted for a review, it would have been curtains for Keegan Petersen.
Short and wide, outside off. Keegan Petersen does not offer any shot to this one.
Good-length ball, well outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Back of a length, angling in from outside off. Keegan Petersen stays back and shoulders his arms to it.
Tosses it up, on middle. Temba Bavuma leans and whips it towards the mid on fielder, along the ground.
On a length, around middle. Keegan Petersen tucks it wide of the mid on fielder for a single.
Slightly short and around off. Keegan Petersen covers his off stump and keeps it out.
This is darted on the pads. Keegan Petersen hangs back and tickles it to short fine leg.
Tossed up, around off. Keegan Petersen gets forward and pushes it to mid on.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Temba Bavuma tucks it wide of the mid-wicket fielder for a run.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Full length, on the pads. Keegan Petersen flicks it into mid-wicket, gets it through the gap and over the ropes.
Back of a length, around off. Keegan Petersen tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full length, outside off. Keegan Petersen drives it to mid off on the front foot.
Full length, on the pads. Temba Bavuma flicks it past mid on for three runs. Placed it really well. Nice balance shown by Temba Bavuma.
On a length, on the fifth stump line. Bavuma blocks it to the off side.
Length ball, on the stumps. Temba Bavuma blocks it out solidly.

DRINKS! Bangladesh have done well to pick a couple of wickets in quick succession post-Lunch. However, the two new batters at the crease look quite settled and Bangladesh must ensure that they do not leak runs and mount pressure on the opposition.
Full and on the stump. Keegan Petersen blocks it off the front foot. Just a single off it.
Fuller, on the fifth stumps. Keegan Petersen shuffles across to block it out.
Length, around off. Temba Bavuma punches it to cover for a single.
On off, Bavuma prods and defends it out.
Full, on the stumps. Temba Bavuma blocks it out watchfully.
Floated and full, outside off. Temba Bavuma drives it to cover.
Fuller, outside off, shapes away a touch. Keegan Petersen gets it back to the bowler off the toe-end.
Full length, on the pads. Keegan Petersen flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace. Keegan Petersen keeping the runs ticking here.
Full, on the off stump. Keegan Petersen bunts it back to the bowler.
Full length, on middle and leg. Keegan Petersen defends it to the leg side.
Length ball, on off. Keegan Petersen blocks it with full face of the blade.

FOUR! These two batters having a go now. It is short, on off. Keegan Petersen swivels and pulls it through mid-wicket for four. This is what Elgar-Erwee managed to do when they were out. Get boundaries at a good rate. These are good signs for South Africa.
FOUR! Nicely played. Temba Bavuma gets his first boundary. Full, on middle and leg. Temba Bavuma waits for it, clips it through mid-wicket. Boundary.
Fuller, on leg. Temba Bavuma flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter, outside off. Temba Bavuma eases it back to the bowler.
Full, on leg. Temba Bavuma flicks it to the leg side.
Loopy ball, around middle. Keegan Petersen flicks it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Fuller, on off, blocked back to the bowler.
Another great over by Khaled Ahmed comes to an end! Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma has no stroke to offer.
Length ball, outside off, nipping in off the deck. Temba Bavuma prods and shoulders his arms at it.
Three dots in a row now! Length ball, on the fifth stump line. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
Length ball, on off. Temba Bavuma dabs it to point.
Swing and a miss! Good-length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma tries to cut it away but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
A full-length ball, on the stumps. Keegan Petersen shuffles across and works it to the right of mid on off the inner half. They take a single.
This is darted on the pads. Keegan Petersen works it behind square on the leg side and settles for a run.
Short and around middle. Bavuma rocks back and tucks it around the corner for a single to get off the mark.
Flatter and turning in from outside off. Temba Bavuma gets back in his crease and dabs it into the deck.
Floated, full and around middle. Temba Bavuma prods and works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, around off. Temba Bavuma blocks it off the front foot.
Temba Bavuma comes in at number 4.

OUT! Chopped on! Two wickets in quick succession for Bangladesh and both the openers are back in the hut now! Terrific passage of play for the Bangla Tigers and Mehidy Hasan is absolutely ecstatic with this dismissal. A false stroke brings about the downfall of Erwee and he walks back disappointed. Coming to the ball - This was tossed up, well outside off. Sarel Erwee gets down on his knee and looks to sweep it from there. He only manages a thick inside edge which cannons onto the stumps. Bangladesh are right back in this contest!
Commentary.Howout: b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Short of a length, around off. Keegan Petersen gets on top of the bounce and keeps it out. End of a successful over for Bangladesh!
Back of a length, around off. Keegan Petersen defends it back to the bowler.
FOUR! A gift from Ahmed. A full ball, on the pads. Keegan Petersen gets forward and flicks it with disdain behind square on the leg side for a boundary. He gets off the mark in style.
BEATEN! A length ball, around the corridor of uncertainty. Keegan Petersen looks to defend off the front foot but the ball nips away a tad and goes past Petersen's blade.
Keegan Petersen is the new batter in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Finally, Bangladesh get the breakthrough and the ploy to bring back Khaled Ahmed into the attack has done wonders for the tourists! That exploded off the pitch and Dean Elgar had absolutely no answers to it. Ahmed runs in and serves it on a length, around off. Elgar looks to go on the front foot to block but the ball takes off from a length and Elgar fails to bail out in the end. The ball goes off his gloves to the left of the keeper. Liton Das moves low to his left and takes a good catch. End of a good innings from the South African skipper.
Commentary.Howout: c Liton Das b Khaled Ahmed

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, around off. Dean Elgar defends it to the off side.
Much slower through the air, full and outside off. Sarel Erwee leans and drives it to the cover fielder.
Looped up, on a length, around off. Sarel Erwee blocks it off the front foot.
Floated, full and outside off. Sarel Erwee keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, just outside off. Sarel Erwee stays low to cut but the ball sneaks through his bat.
Tosses it up, on middle. Sarel Erwee pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Swept away! Tossed up, down leg. Erwee kneels and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Crunched but for no run! Short of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar hangs back and cuts hard. The fielder at backward point dives and saves a certain boundary.
Hossain errs in line and spills it down leg. Dean Elgar looks to work it around the corner but he misses.
An appeal for LBW but turned down by the umpire! A full ball, on middle. Dean Elgar looks to flick but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.

BEATEN! That is a peach of a delivery from Ebadot Hossain! This one lands on a length, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar tries to block it off the front foot but the ball jags away late and zips past Elgar's outside edge.
Good-length ball, just outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it to cover off the front foot. Not in the gap though!
A full ball, on middle. Dean Elgar leans and drives it to the mid on fielder.
Slower through the air, on a length, outside off. Erwee gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Erwee gets forward and blocks it solidly.
Fuller in length, on off. Erwee drives it back past the bowler towards  mid on.
Slightly shorter in length, outside off. Dean Elgar rocks back and punches it down to long off for a single.
Floats it up, on middle. Elgar prods and works it towards mid on.
Flatter ball, outside off. Dean Elgar stays back and cuts it towards point.
Good length, on off. Sarel Erwee closes the face of the blade, works it to mid-wicket. A maiden for Ebadot Hossain now.
Full length, on off. Sarel Erwee bunts it back to the bowler on a bounce. Ebadot Hossain leaps and gets fingertips on it.
Length ball, on the stumps, Sarel Erwee flicks it to the leg side.
Full, outside off. Sarel Erwee works it to mid off.

This is much better from Ebadot Hossain! A length ball, pitching on leg, it climbs off the deck. Sarel Erwee is caught inside the crease and gets struck on his thigh bad. Ebadot Hossain appeals but the umpire is unmoved. The replays show that the ball had pitched outside leg as well.
Full length, on the fifth stump, angled across. Sarel Erwee blocks it to the off side.
Touch quicker, darted on the pads. Dean Elgar stays back and blocks it out.
Full, around middle. Elgar flicks it to mid on.
On the stumps. Dean Elgar eases it to mid on.
Short ball, on the fifth stump. Elgar punches it to cover.
Flatter and outside off. Sarel Erwee cuts it to point for one more.
Short ball, outside off. Dean Elgar works it to point for a single.
Length ball, on off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out watchfully.
Full length, on middle and leg. Sarel Erwee flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Fuller, wide outside off. Sarel Erwee tries to chase it away but misses. He gets beaten by pace this time.
Outside off, left alone by Erwee.
Good length, a bit to straight, on the pads. Dean Elgar glances it down the corner for one more.
Length ball, on off. Sarel Erwee pushes it to cover for a single.

FOUR! What a shot! Pleasing to the eyes! Fuller, on middle and leg. Dean Elgar steps forward and drives it to long on for a boundary. The first boundary comes off the spinner in the afternoon session. 100 comes up for the Proteas!
Fuller, outside off. Dean Elgar shuffles across and bunts it to the off side.
Touch short, outside off. Sarel Erwee cuts it to point for a single.
Tosses it up, on off. Sarel Erwee works it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on off. Sarel Erwee defends it on the front foot.
Looped up, on the stumps. Sarel Erwee blocks it out solidly.
Full, on the pads. Dean Elgar tucks it to mid-wicket. A great start for Ebadot Hossain. He avoids being hit for a boundary this time.
Full, on the stumps. Elgar bunts it back to the bowler.
Full-length ball, on off. Dean Elgar works it towards mid on.

Slight halt in play. The wicketkeeper looks in pain. Liton Das seems to have hurt his right wrist in an attempt to stop the ball and the physio comes out to have a check on him. Das looks good to go now.
TWO BYES! Fuller, angling down leg. Dean Elgar fails to clip it away. Liton Das also fails to gather the same. The batters take two byes to fine leg.
It is full and on the off stump. Dean Elgar blocks it to mid off.

A full toss, on leg, Dean Elgar tries to flick it away but ends up playing all around it. Ebadot Hossain makes a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Mominul Haque decides to take the review with one second remaining on the timer. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking shows the impact is outside the line. Dean Elgar survives, as Bangladesh lose a review here. A juicy start to the post-Lunch session.

We are all set for the second session to get underway! The players have made their way out to the middle. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee will resume their innings. Ebadot Hossain will start with the ball.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

The first session has completely belonged to South Africa and Bangladesh will need to bounce back hard in the next session. Will the Bangla Tigers be able to make early inroads in the second session? We shall find that soon. Do join us for the middle session which begins at 4.40 pm IST (11.10 am GMT).

Bangladesh's pacers didn't start well and they failed to make use of the red cherry early on. They were all over the place with their lines and lengths and South Africa's openers took full advantage of it. Dean Elgar was the aggressor, while Erwee took time to get his eye in. Bangladesh will need to break this opening stand as soon as possible in the post-Lunch session if they are to restrict the Proteas to a reasonable total in the first innings.

What a morning this has been for South Africa! The opening pair of Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee has stitched together an unbeaten stand of 95 runs and Lunch will certainly taste better for the hosts. That dropped catch by Liton Das behind the sticks just at the stroke of Lunch has ensured that South Africa dominate the first session of Day 1.
Fuller, outside off. Sarel Erwee drives it to cover. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1.
Full, on off, defended out solidly.

DROPPED! Oh dear, a beautiful chance, just before Lunch. It is short, outside off, turns away a bit. Sarel Erwee tries to cut it away on the back foot. It takes the outside edge, although Liton Das is unable to pouch it behind the stumps.
Short ball, outside off. Dean Elgar cuts it to deep point for a single.
Full, on middle and leg. Dean Elgar flicks it to mid on.
Flighted, full and outside off. Dean Elgar drives it to cover.
Short ball, on top of off. Sarel Erwee blocks it to the left of the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely played! Full length, on the pads. Sarel Erwee flicks it through square leg for a boundary. Boundaries continue to come for South Africa.
Just short of mid on! Touch short, outside off. Sarel Erwee tries to pull it away but does not middle it. The ball flies towards mid on off the outer half but lands short of Taskin Ahmed there.
A length ball, on off, defended to mid on.
Short ball, on off. Elgar flicks it to the leg side for a single.
FOUR! Hammered away! Dean Elgar continues on his merry way. It is a short ball, outside off. Dean Elgar stays back and pulls it away in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Short ball, on off. Erwee blocks it to point.
Full, outside off. Sarel Erwee prods and defends it back to the bowler.
Short ball, outside off. Dean Elgar punches it to the off side for a single.
Floated, on middle and leg. Elgar goes back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full, on off. Elgar leans and flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Fuller, on off, defended to cover.
FOUR! EDGY! Full length, angled into off. Sarel Erwee tries to defend it out. It takes the thick outside edge, races away past gully and into the fence.
Good length, outside off. Sarel Erwee bunts it to cover.
Length ball, on the pads, Sarel Erwee flicks it to the leg side.
Short and on off. Elgar pulls it to square leg for a single.
Fuller, outside off, Dean Elgar drives it to point but straight to the fielder.
Length ball, on off. Dean Elgar defends it to cover off the outer half.
Short, outside off. Dean Elgar punches it to cover for a single.
Tap and run! Good running. Overpitched, outside off. Sarel Erwee drives it to mid off for one.
Outside off, Sarel Erwee taps it to the off side.
Fuller, on leg. Sarel Erwee gets low and sweeps it to short fine leg.
Looped up, outside off. Sarel Erwee slaps it to cover but straight to the fielder.
Fuller, outside off. Sarel Erwee blocks it to point.
Good-length ball, around off. Dean Elgar prods and defends it out.
A short ball, around leg. Elgar ducks underneath.
This is another full ball, around middle. Sarel Erwee flicks it to the fielder at deep square leg for a single.
Full and angling across the batter. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
FOUR! Pulled away! A bumper, around leg. Erwee hangs back and pulls it behind square on the leg side for a boundary. Two fielders in the deep but they had no chance of cutting it off.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Dean Elgar tucks it around the corner and settles for a run.
This is darted on the pads. Sarel Erwee glances it through the fine leg region and takes a couple of runs.

Full and outside off. Dean Elgar drives it, a bit uppishly through cover for a run. FIFTY up for the South African skipper! He raises his bat as he gets a round of applause from his teammates in the dressing room. The skipper is certainly leading from the front at Kingsmead!
Slightly shorter in length, going on with the angle, from middle. Dean Elgar tucks it to mid-wicket.
Floated, full and around middle. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
A loosener from Mehidy Hasan, short and outside off. Dean Elgar cuts it past the point fielder for a brace.
Mehidy starts with a flatter ball, around off. Dean Elgar keeps it out.
Time for some spin as Mehidy Hasan comes into the attack.
Full length, on off. Sarel Erwee blocks it back to the bowler on the front foot.
On a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee blocks it to mid off.
Length ball, on the pads. Sarel Erwee flicks it to long leg for a brace.
What a beauty! A length ball, pitching on leg. It holds its line. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it. The ball brushes his thigh pads and goes to the keeper.
Back of a length, on leg. Erwee tucks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, angled across the left hander. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller, wide outside off. Sarel Erwee drives it to cover for a quick single.
Full length, outside off. Sarel Erwee tries to drive it away. The ball takes an inside edge onto the pads.
This is fuller, angled in on off. Sarel Erwee blocks it watchfully.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump. Sarel Erwee dabs it to point.
Touch short, outside off. Sarel Erwee pulls it to mid on off the bottom end.
Good length, on off. Dean Elgar flicks it to mid-wicket and scampers across for a run.
Full length, on off. Sarel Erwee blocks it back to the bowler.
This is a touch fuller, outside off. Sarel Erwee covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
