Full length, aimed straight at the pads. Sarel Erwee tucks it to square leg.
NO BALL! Length ball, on off. Erwee defends it out solidly. The umpire signals a no ball as Taskin Ahmed oversteps.

BEATEN! Oh, what a beauty! Looks like Taskin Ahmed has found his ideal length here. It is a good-length ball, pitching on middle and leg. It nips away sharply off the deck. Sarel Erwee gets squared up, as the ball zips past the outside edge.
Length ball, outside off. Erwee pushes it to cover.
Now, Khaled Ahmed ends his over with a dot! Fuller, outside off, it climbs off the deck. Dean Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper.
NO BALL! Full length, on off. Dean Elgar defends it out watchfully. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Short ball, outside off, left alone by Elgar.
Full length, on the fourth stump. Dean Elgar shuffles across and tucks it to mid on.
Length ball, on off, Elgar defends it out.
Half an appeal! Length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar dashes but is fortunate to survive. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Khaled Ahmed persisting with the angle from 'round the wicket. Angled in, around off. Elgar blocks it to the off side.
Good length, around off. Erwee blocks it out solidly. Taskin Ahmed starts his second stint with a maiden.
Fuller, outside off. Erwee drives it to mid off, but unable to pierce the gap.
This is much closer, still a little wider for Erwee to leave it. Length ball, on the fourth stump, angled across, with some extra bounce. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms.
Taskin Ahmed continues to bowl wide outside off and Erwee has no intentions of chasing away from his body.
Good length, wide outside off. Sarel Erwee has no stroke to offer.
Back of a length, outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.

DRINKS! South Africa have gotten off to an excellent start and their skipper, Dean Elgar is looking in fine touch. Sarel Erwee too, has held one end nicely and this opening stand is proving to be threatening for the tourists. Bangladesh's bowlers have lacked consistency so far and they need to get the breakthrough as early as possible. Taskin Ahmed comes back to bowl now. Will he provide the breakthrough in his second spell?
It is a length ball, angled into the pads. Dean Elgar blocks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball, on off. Elgar defends it to cover. Khaled Ahmed is able to maintain good line and length after tweaking the angle.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar guides it past gully for a brace.
Full length, sliding into off. Dean Elgar blocks it out solidly.

Khaled Ahmed continues to come 'round the wicket. He angles in a full delivery, on off. Sarel Erwee defends it to the leg side off the inner half. The batters take a quick single. Good use of the angle by Khaled Ahmed. Will it pay off though?
Full length, angled in, on off. Sarel Erwee defends it on the front foot.
FOUR! Third boundary of the over. South Africa are off to a flying start, Short ball, wide outside off. Elgar rides the bounce and cuts it through point for a cracking boundary.
This one is down the leg side. Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper.
Short ball, around off. Dean Elgar blocks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. Also, 50 comes up for South Africa, while Elgar moves to 40 off 40. It is full, on leg. Dean Elgar flicks it behind square on the leg side for four.

FOUR! Dean Elgar is on a roll here. He uses the pace of the ball really well this time. Good-length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar stays back and punches it through point for a boundary. He seems to be in good touch.
Short ball, on off. Elgar hops and defends it out.
Length ball, on the fifth stump. Sarel Erwee gets behind the line and blocks it back to the bowler.
Yet another good leave! Back of a length, wide outside off, nips in a little late. Sarel Erwee shuffles across and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. It climbs off the deck. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at it.
A length ball, on off. Erwee presses forward and defends it to cover.
This is sliding down the leg side, on a length. Extracts some extra bounce as well. Erwee fails to work it around the corner.
FOUR! Sarel Erwee finding his feet now. It is a short ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee rocks back and pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
FOUR! Top shot! Width offered, outside off. Dean Elgar gets on top of the bounce and punches it hard past the extra cover fielder for a boundary.
This is a wayward ball, angling down leg. Dean Elgar sways away from the line of the ball.
Back of a length, just outside off. Dean Elgar taps it past the backward point fielder and comes back for the second run. Good intent shown by the batters.

FOUR! Shouts of catch it, but that went way over the gully region! Back of a length, outside off. Elgar tries to play it away from his body, and looks to punch it through cover. It takes the thick outside edge and flies over the gully fielder for a boundary.
Good-length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar lets it through to the keeper.

Leg bye! A full ball, around leg. Sarel Erwee misses his flick and gets hit on his pad. The ball rolls away behind square on the leg side for a leg bye. A stifled appeal but that was surely heading down leg.
Full and outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
Back of a length, around off. Dean Elgar keeps it out.
FOUR! Easy pickings for Dean Elgar! Ahmed strays on the pads. Elgar flicks it nonchalantly past the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Ahmed drags his length back a bit, just outside off. Dean Elgar lets it sail through to the keeper.
Another ball that is full and around off. Dean Elgar keeps it out.
Full and outside off. Sarel Erwee drives hard but the fielder at cover half-stops it and the batters take a single.
This is darted on the pads, from over the wicket. Dean Elgar misses his flick and gets hit near his hips.
Drop and run! Short of a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee taps it towards backward point and scampers through to the other end.
On a length, around off. Erwee dabs it onto the deck.

BEAUTY! That cut the batter in half! This is a back-of-a-length ball that nips back in sharply, from outside off. Erwee hangs back to block but the ball sneaks through the gap between his bat and pad.
Good-length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.

FOUR! Top effort in the deep by Taskin Ahmed but it goes in vain in the end! A full ball, around leg. Sarel Erwee clips it behind square on the leg side. Taskin runs across to his right, puts in a dive to stop the ball but he fails to do so.
FOUR! Edgy! Short of a length, around the corridor of uncertainty. Elgar looks to defend but it goes off the thick outside edge, past the diving fielder at gully for a boundary.
Back of a length, well outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone watchfully.
Fuller in length, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.

On a length and jagging back in late from outside off. Dean Elgar looks to defend at first but sways away from the line of the delivery in the end. The ball goes just past his outside edge. Well bowled!
Full and outside off. Dean Elgar prods but lets it sail through to the keeper.
On a good length, around off. Dean Elgar covers his line and keeps it out.
Another ball, short of a length, around off. Sarel Erwee blocks it out, off the back foot.
On a length, jagging back in from middle. Elgar nudges it wide of the mid-wicket fielder and settles for a single.
Slightly shorter in length, jagging back in late from outside off. Elgar stays back to block but he misses and gets hit on his elbow.
Hossain pitches it right up, outside off. Elgar runs down the track but lets it through to the keeper.
Full and outside off. Dean Elgar lets it be.
Back of a length, nipping back in from off. Dean Elgar stays back and tucks it awkwardly towards backward square leg.
Good-length ball, just outside off. Sarel Erwee does not bother playing at that one.
Back of a length, around off. Sarel Erwee dabs it to the off side.
Taskin changes his angle and comes over the wicket. He serves a full ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it alone.
A length ball, angling in from off. Dean Elgar sits back and flicks it wide of the mid-wicket fielder for a single.
On a length, outside off and staying a touch low. Dean Elgar covers his off stump and lets it be.
On a length and way outside off. Dean Elgar lets it through to the keeper.
A bit full and around middle. Sarel Erwee defends it off the front foot.
This is a length ball, outside off. Sarel Erwee shoulders his arms at this one.
On a length, around off. Sarel Erwee hangs back and blocks it onto the deck.
Short of a length, angling in from outside off. Sarel Erwee offers no shot to it.
Good-length ball, around off. Sarel Erwee keeps it out watchfully.
Fuller in length, well outside off. Erwee leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Elgar does not bother playing at that one.
Pitches it up, just outside off. Elgar looks to drive but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
Short of a length, around leg. Elgar hangs back and nudges it behind square on the leg side for a brace.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Just a punch down the ground! A bit full, around off. Elgar prods and just works it back past the bowler through mid off. The fielder there gives it a chase but the ball wins.
Drags his length back a bit, just outside off. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at this one.
Fuller in length, around the fourth stump. Elgar leans and defends it towards cover.
This is a good-length ball, nipping back in from middle. Erwee misses his flick and gets hit high on his pad.
Back of a length, jagging back in from outside off. Sarel Erwee leaves it but the ball comes back in sharply and brushes his thigh pad before going to the keeper.
Hossain errs in line this time and serves a wayward ball, angling down leg. Sarel Erwee misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Hossain persists with short of a length stuff, around off. Sarel Erwee stays back and dabs it onto the deck.
Another ball, on a length, angling in from outside off. Sarel Erwee covers his off pole and keeps it out.
Erwee is off the mark straightaway! Back of a length, outside off. Sarel Erwee stays back and taps it behind square on the off side. The fielder at gully misfields and they take two runs.
Ebadot Hossain to bowl from the other end.
Good-length ball, angling across the batter. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
This is a length ball that jags back in from middle. Dean Elgar tucks it around the corner and takes a couple of runs.
A full ball, around leg. Elgar prods and flicks it towards mid-wicket.

A loud appeal for lbw, turned down! A length ball, pitching on middle and leg. Angled across the left-hander. Dean Elgar gets squared up inside the crease and misses to defend it out. He gets pinged above his pads. Maybe missing the stumps. Nonetheless, a beautiful delivery by Taskin Ahmed.
Another one, angled down the leg side. Dean Elgar fails to get any bat on it.
FOUR! Nice start for South Africa and Dean Elgar. A length ball, on the pads. Dean Elgar flicks it through square leg for a boundary.

UPDATE - 1.50 pm IST (8.20 am GMT) - The start of play has been delayed due to some technical issue with the sight screen. The players of Bangladesh have made their way back to the dugout. Dean Elgar is seen having a chat with the on-field umpire. We hope that the issue is sorted out soon. Stay tuned for further updates. Right then, the players are back on the field and we are set for Day 1 to begin, finally!

We are done with all the pre-match formalities and it is time for the game to begin! The players of Bangladesh are in a huddle before they stride out to the middle. Dean Elgar and Sarel Erwee are at the crease. The players of both sides take a knee to show their support for the 'BLM' movement. Taskin Ahmed will start proceedings with the ball. Just as the game is about to get underway, there seems to be some issue with the sight screen. The groundstaff are trying to cover the sight screen with white sheets now. Ohhhh, wait! The sheets that are being used to cover the sight screen are transparent and we might have to wait a bit longer for Day 1 to get underway. There are some black patches on the sight screen and the groundstaff are doing their best to sort that out.
The players from both sides have lined up for their respective national anthems. It will be Bangladesh's anthem first, followed by the anthem of South Africa.

Dean Elgar, the skipper of South Africa, says we are used to seeing grass on the deck at Kingsmead. Adds that they are not too displeased with the grass and they were any way looking to bat first. Tells that they are playing two spinners and hopes that they can make the most of it as the game progresses. Adds, there are a few debutants in the side. States that Ryan Rickelton, the debutant, will bat at number 5.

Mominul Haque, the skipper of Bangladesh, says there is some grass on the deck with some moisture as well. Adds, they will try to apply some pressure. Mentions, Shakib Al Hasan misses due to a niggle. Also adds that it is a good moment for the young players to step up with opportunity in place.

South Africa (Playing XI) - Dean Elgar (C), Sarel Erwee, Keegan Petersen, Temba Bavuma, Ryan Rickelton (On Debut), Kyle Verreynne (WK), Wiaan Mulder, Keshav Maharaj, Simon Harmer, Lizaad Williams (On Debut), Duanne Olivier.

Bangladesh (Playing XI) - Mominul Haque (C), Shadman Islam, Mahmudul Hasan Joy, Najmul Hossain Shanto, Mushfiqur Rahim, Liton Das (WK), Yasir Ali, Mehidy Hasan, Taskin Ahmed, Khaled Ahmed, Ebadot Hossain.
TOSS - Bangladesh have won the toss and they have elected to BOWL first.

There are plenty of new faces in the South African unit but they also have the experience of skipper Dean Elgar, Temba Bavuma and Keshav Maharaj. The Proteas have included some exciting young pacers in their ranks and they would be itching to take the field in the absence of Kagiso Rabada and Anrich Nortje. Bangladesh on the other hand, are playing with a full-strength squad and they would be keen to repeat their heroics of New Zealand and put the hosts under pressure in this first Test. Lots of things to look forward to in this exciting Test. Stay tuned for toss and further updates.

Hello and a very warm welcome to the coverage of Day 1 of the first Test between Bangladesh and South Africa. After clinching the ODI series 2-1, Bangladesh would be eager to carry on with the winning momentum and start the Test series on a positive note against a depleted South African side. It promises to be a fascinating contest between two relatively young sides and it'll be interesting to see who gains advantage on the first day of this Test series.
... Day 1, Session 1 ...
We are back for the third innings of this Test. The players have made their way out to the middle. Sarel Erwee and Dean Elgar are at the crease. Khaled Ahmed will start with the ball.
... Third innings ...

Bangladesh batted well in patches and Joy did manage to stitch some crucial partnerships with Najmul Hossain Shanto, Liton Das and Mehidy Hasan. However, the tourists failed to get a big partnership and that kept them away from getting close to South Africa's total. If not for Joy, Bangladesh would have been bowled out much early. For South Africa, it was their spinners that kept things tight and it was Simon Harmer who grabbed 4 wickets on Day 2. Keshav Maharaj bowled his heart out and even though he failed to get into the wickets column, he proved to be extremely economical. The debutant, Lizaad Williams picked three wickets on Day 3 but overall, South Africa could have been much better with the ball. The South African batters will now look to see off the new ball and stretch the lead as far as possible. Will the Bangladesh bowlers make early inroads? Stay tuned, as we find that out soon.

What an innings this has been from Mahmudul Hasan Joy! He has ensured that South Africa does not get a massive first innings lead. South Africa do get a lead of 69 in the end, but they would be disappointed as they were made to toil hard by the Bangladeshi lower middle-order batters.

OUT! CAUGHT! A valiant knock of Joy comes to an end. Lizaad Williams picks up his third wicket of the innings. It is a short ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy throws his blade at it. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the man at first slip. Simon Harmer takes a stunning catch. BANGLADESH GET BUNDLED OUT AT 298.
Commentary.Howout: c Simon Harmer b Lizaad Williams

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR BYES! Free runs for Bangladesh. A length ball, outside off. It stays low off the deck. Mahmudul Hasan Joy slashes hard but it sneaks under his blade. The ball goes through the keeper for a boundary. The umpire signals byes.
A yorker, angled into off. Joy digs it out watchfully.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it to deep square leg but does not run to the other end.
Full length, on the stumps. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it to the leg side.
Ebadot Hossain is the last batter in.

Short ball, on off. Khaled Ahmed tries to defend it out but it looks like he pulls his blade back in time. Duanne Olivier and company appeal for caught behind. The keeper is really excited after the take. The umpire though does not raise his finger. South Africa take a review for caught behind. The UltraEdge confirms that there is a spike as the ball passes the glove. The on-field decision is forced to be overturned. Khaled Ahmed walks back to the pavilion.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Duanne Olivier

Commentary.Commentary: Duanne Olivier bends his back and serves a short ball, on off. Khaled Ahmed tries to sway away from the line but takes a blow on his body.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Khaled Ahmed leans back and leaves it alone for the keeper.
A yorker length delivery, on middle and leg. Khaled Ahmed digs it out solidly.
Full length, on off. Khaled Ahmed flicks it to mid on.
Full length, angled down leg. Khaled Ahmed fails to flick it off his pads. He gets pinged, Duanne Olivier appeals but the umpire is unmoved.

FOUR! Mahmudul Hasan Joy ends the over by bagging the fourth boundary. It is a short ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy waits for it and guides it smartly through the slip cordon for four. The deficit now goes down to 73.
Full length, on middle and leg. Joy tucks it to short mid-wicket. He could not get the single he was looking for.
FOUR! Three on the trot! It is a short ball, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. Mahmudul Hasan Joy is displaying great skills. Full length, wide outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy strides and lifts it over mid off for another boundary.
FOUR! Mahmudul Hasan Joy has only one job now. He is certainly taking the attack to South Africa now. Full length, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets under it and lofts it over mid off for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy tries to punch it to the off side. The ball takes the under edge and goes towards the keeper.
Really good batting by Joy! It is short and outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy steers it to short third man for a single. Joy to retain the strike.
On off, blocked back to the bowler.
FOUR! Short and punished! Mahmudul Hasan Joy is on a roll. It is short, around middle and leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy makes some room, latches onto it and cuts it hard through covers for a boundary.
Full, on the stumps. Joy defends it back to the bowler.
SIX! BANG! Mahmudul Hasan Joy talking with his blade now. This is full and outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy kneels and slogs it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Fuller, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy reverse-hits it to cover.
Full length, on the pads. Ahmed clips it to the leg side.
Khaled Ahmed walks out to bat.

OUT! CAUGHT AT SLIPS! Wiaan Mulder strikes and breaks a crucial stand for his side. It is an outswinging delivery, full and outside off. Mehidy Hasan goes for the expansive drive but does not middle it. In fact, the ball takes the outside edge and flies straight into the palms of Simon Harmer at first slip who makes no mistake. Although, there was a slight halt in celebration as the umpire wanted to check the front foot. The replays suggest that it is a legal delivery. Can South Africa end things quickly for Bangladesh?
Commentary.Howout: c Simon Harmer b Wiaan Mulder

Commentary.Commentary: OH DEAR! Mehidy Hasan is fortunate this time. Back of a length, on off. Hasan tries to pull his bat back but is a tad late to do so. The ball bumps into the deck and sneaks past the stumps.
Good length, outside off, it nips away sharply off the deck. Mehidy Hasan does not go fishing away from his body.
FOUR! Mehidy Hasan stepping on the gas here. It is full and outside off. Mehidy Hasan leans in and creams it through covers for a boundary.
Full length, angled into off. Hasan defends it to cover.
Full, on middle and leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays back and clips it to short leg.
Tossed up, full and on leg. Joy defends it out watchfully.
On off, Joy prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller, outside off. Joy drives it to the right of mid off. The fielder there moves to that side and makes an excellent stop.
Angled into the pads. Joy tucks it to the leg side.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Joy guides it to third man for a brace.
A yorker-length ball, around off. Mehidy Hasan digs it out watchfully. A maiden over from Wiaan Mulder!
Fuller in length, around off. Mehidy Hasan keeps it out.
Pitches it up, around off. Hasan gets solid in his defence.
This is on a length, around middle. Mehidy Hasan gets right behind the line of the ball to defend.
On a length and angling in from middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it off the back foot.
Good-length ball, around off. Mehidy Hasan defends it towards point.

Is that dropped? Tossed up, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to block off the front foot. He gets a thick outside edge towards Keegan Petersen who is a bit late to react. He gets fingertips to it but fails to grab it cleanly.
Flighted delivery, around off. Mehidy Hasan drives it through the cover region for a single.
Floated, on a length, around middle. Mehidy Hasan blocks it.
An overpitched ball, on middle. Mehidy Hasan squeezes it out to mid on.
Flatter ball, on a length and turning in from off. Mehidy Hasan gets right back to defend it.
Flatter ball, outside off. Mehidy Hasan stays back to cut but he misses.
Simon Harmer to bowl from the other end.
On a length, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it with ease.
Uppish but safe! A length ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy chips it just past the cover fielder and collects a couple of runs.
Fuller in length, just outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out, off the front foot.
No Ball! On a length and outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone. The umpire calls it no ball as the bowler oversteps.
Fuller in length, angling in from middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy leans and works it to mid on.
A full ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it to the mid off fielder.

Mulder starts with a full ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy reaches out and slices it towards the gully fielder, on the bounce. A stifled appeal for catch and the umpires have sent it upstairs. The replays clearly suggest that it was a bump ball.

We are back for the third session of Day 3! The players have made their way out to the middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy and Mehidy Hasan will resume their innings. Wiaan Mulder will start the proceedings with the ball. Let's go...
... Day 3, Session 3 ...

For South Africa, it was Lizaad Williams who struck straight after the Lunch break and sent back well-set Liton Das for 41. Although, the Proteas have been a tad inconsistent in the second session and the spinners, Simon Harmer and Keshav Maharaj have toiled hard to go past the defenses of Mahmudul Hasan Joy, but to no avail. The Proteas did manage to run out Yasir Ali but since then, nothing has gone their way. The partnership between Mehidy Hasan and Mahmudul Hasan Joy is now worth 41 and Bangladesh would hope that they carry on and get as close to South Africa's total as possible. Do join us for the final session of Day 3 which begins at 6.30 pm IST (1 pm GMT).

Mahmudul Hasan Joy continues to frustrate South Africa! This has been a terrific innings from Joy so far and not to forget the contributions of Yasir Ali and Mehidy Hasan. They have managed to keep South Africa's spinners at bay and have scored 74 runs from 28 overs in this session, at the cost of two wickets.
Fuller, outside off. Mehidy Hasan steps forward and drives it to mid off. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 3.
Five dots on the trot now! Floated, full and on leg. Hasan remains solid in his defense.
Angled into the pads, Hasan tucks it to short leg.
On off, Hasan defends it forward on the front foot.
Full, on the pads, Hasan clips it to short leg.
Fuller, on off. Hasan lunges and blocks it to silly point.
On off, defended out.
NO BALL! Fuller, on off. Joy blocks it back to the bowler. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.
Keshav Maharaj has hurt his spinning finger. He is bleeding and he has a chat with the umpire. He won't be allowed to strap the spinning finger.
Full, on the pads. Mahmudul Hasan Joy flicks it over mid-wicket for two runs.
Tossed up, around middle and leg. Joy defends it to short leg off the inner half.
Fuller, on the pads. Joy blocks it to short leg.
Fuller, outside off. Joy drives it to wide of long off for a brace.
Full and on off. Joy defends it into the deck.
On off, blocked out.
Just evades the short leg fielder. It is quicker, on the pads. Hasan goes back to defend it out. He gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball goes to the right of the short leg fielder.
Flatter, outside off. Hasan blocks it out watchfully.
Loopy ball, around middle and leg. Hasan prods to block it out.
Tossed up, full and outside off. Hasan leans in and defends it to the off side.
Full and on the stumps. Mehidy Hasan blocks it out with full face.
Full length, on middle and leg. Joy eases it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off. Joy dabs it to point.
The dots continue to creep up. This time it is sharp bouncer, on off. Joy ducks under it watchfully.
Fuller, on the stumps. Joy smothers it back to the bowler.
Full length, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it gently to mid off.
Outside off. Joy pushes it to mid off.
Short and outside off. Hasan pucnhes it to cover.
Floated, full and on the pads. Hasan tucks it to short leg yet again.
Around leg. Hasan clips it to short leg.
Flighted, onto the pads. Hasan defends it out by pressing forward.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Hasan blocks it back to the bowler.
On off, defended out solidly.
Halt in play. Mahmudul Hasan Joy seems to be having some issue with his right ankle. The physio is out to have a check on him. He looks fine now and we are good to go.
On a length, outside off. Joy leaves it alone for the keeper.
Length ball, on off. Joy defends it to the off side.
Full length, on off, Joy defends it out solidly.
Full, on the pads, Hasan clips it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. The stand moves to 35. A short ball, outside off yet again. Mehidy Hasan slashes hard at it. It goes past gully and into the third man fence.
FOUR! Top shot! Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan cuts it over point and bags a boundary.

Edged but safe! Floated, full and around middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to defend off the front foot. The ball spins away, takes the outside edge and goes past the first slip fielder for a couple of runs.
Around off. Blocked out.
Nicely tossed up, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out.
Bye! A full ball, down leg. Mehidy Hasan misses his sweep and the keeper fails to grab the ball cleanly. The batters cross for a bye.
FOUR! Easy pickings! A flatter ball, around leg. Hasan gets forward and just tickles it through the fine leg region for a boundary.
This is full and down leg. Mehidy Hasan gets down on his knee and sweeps it straight to the short fine leg fielder.
This is darted on the pads. Mehidy Hasan tucks it around the corner and rotates the strike.
Good-length delivery, around off. Mehidy Hasan keeps it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan lets it sail through to the keeper.
On a length and well outside off. Mehidy Hasan lets it be.
Shorter in length, around off. Mehidy Hasan defends it solidly.
Back of a length, around off. Mehidy Hasan gets on top of the bounce and blocks it.
Floated, full and around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy dead-bats it. Back-to-back maiden overs for South Africa!
Flighted delivery, around off. Joy defends it off the front foot.
Floated, full and around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out watchfully.
A full ball, around middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy clears his front leg and whips it towards square leg.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Blocked out.
Just short of the short leg fielder! Tossed up, on middle. Joy looks to block it with hard hands. It hits the splice of his bat and lands just in front of Sarel Erwee at short leg.
On off, Hasan defends it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Hasan lunges and defends it forward.
Darted on the pads, Hasan clips it to the leg side.
Flatter, on middle. Hasan remains solid in his defense.
On the pads, Hasan goes back and blocks it to the leg side.
Fuller, on the stumps. Hasan tucks it to the left of short leg.
On the pads, Joy flicks it to square leg.

HUNDRED FOR JOY! What a fine, fine knock this has been from the Bangladeshi opener! He becomes the first Bangladesh player to score a century against South Africa in Test cricket. This is a flatter ball, outside off. Joy cuts it through the point region and comes back for the second run. He removes his helmet, raises his bat towards the dressing room. His teammates are ecstatic and they give a round of applause to what has been a terrific knock from the youngster. Joy though would be looking to bat deep and take his team to a much better position from hereon.

A direct hit at the bowler's end but Mahmudul Hasan Joy makes it home. This is tossed up, around off. Joy pushes it to mid off and takes a single. A direct hit at the non-striker's end and the ball ricochets off the stumps towards the leg side. The batters steal another run. Joy moves to 98.
Around off, blocked out.
Tossed up, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy plants his front foot forward and dabs it onto the deck.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up, around off. Mehidy Hasan defends it out.
SIX! Mehidy Hasan breaks the shackles! This is tossed up, around middle. Hasan kneels and slog-sweeps it over the deep mid-wicket region for a maximum. Excellent shot!
Floated, on a length, around middle, from 'round the wicket. Mehidy Hasan gets forward and blocks it.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Mehidy Hasan rocks back and dead-bats it.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Mehidy Hasan keeps it out.
A quicker ball, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy tucks it to mid-wicket and takes a quick single.
Full, on off. Hasan defends it to off side.
Around off, defended to cover.
Tossed up, on off. Hasan defends it watchfully.
On off, defended to cover.
Full, on off. Hasan blocks it in front of him.
Full, on the stumps. Hasan prods and blocks it out.
Quicker, full, on the pads. Joy flicks it to square leg.
Full, on off, defended out watchfully.
Full, on middle and leg. Joy defends it to short leg off the inner half.
Tosses it up, on the stumps. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it back to the bowler.
Wide outside off. Hasan pushes it to cover on the front foot. They take one.
Fuller, on off. Hasan blocks it to the right of the bowler.
Full and on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy remains solid in his defense.
Tosses it up, on off. Joy prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Looped up, full and on off. Hasan pushes it to cover for a quick single.
Full, on off. Hasan prods and blocks it to silly point.
Fuller, on off, Hasan blocks it out watchfully.
Looped up, on the pads. Hasan tucks it to the leg side.
Joy does see off this over really well. It is full, on middle and leg. Joy leans forward and clips it square on the leg side.
Angled into the pads. Joy tucks it to short leg.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Joy clips it to mid-wicket.
Fuller, on the pads, Joy goes back and tucks it to the leg side.
FOUR! EDGY! It is tossed up, wide outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy throws the blade at it. The ball races away to the third man fence off the outside edge. He moves to 95.
Fuller, on off. Joy dances down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.

DRINKS! Mahmudul Hasan Joy has held one end really well for Bangladesh but South Africa has managed to get a couple of wickets in the first hour of the second session. The tourists still trail by 149 runs and they would hope that Mahmudul Hasan Joy bats deep into the innings along with the lower order batters.
On a length, outside off. Hasan punches it to point.
Back of a length, outside off. Mehidy Hasan dabs it to point.
Outside off, left alone by Hasan.
Short ball, angled down the leg side. Mehidy Hasan leaves it alone for the keeper.
A length ball, on top of off. Hasan blocks it back to the bowler with full face.
Back of a length, on off. Mehidy Hasan hops inside the crease and blocks it out to cover.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets back in his crease and dabs it onto the deck.
Edged but safe! Flighted delivery, outside off. Mehidy Hasan covers his off pole and looks to block. It takes the outside edge and goes past the slip fielder for a single.
Tosses it up, around middle. Hasan blocks it off the front foot.
Floated, on a length, around off. Hasan dead-bats it.
BEATEN! A flatter ball, landing just outside off and going on with the arm. Mehidy Hasan looks to block but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Tossed up, on off. Mehidy Hasan keeps it out.
A length ball, shaping in from outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy shoulders his arms to this one.
On a length, shaping away from outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it through to the keeper.
Short of a length, well outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy does not bother playing at that one.
On a length, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy lets it be.
Good-length ball, around leg. Mehidy Hasan tucks it to the leg side for a run.
Mehidy Hasan is the new batter in.

OUT! RUN OUT! Oh, dear! This is the last thing that Bangladesh would have wanted at this stage! A huge mix-up in the middle and it is Yasir Ali who has to walk back to the hut. This was a length ball, around leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy tucks it towards deep mid-wicket and gets to the other end. Yasir Ali though looks to sneak in another run. Mahmudul Hasan Joy is not interested and he doesn't go for it. Ryan Rickelton in the deep throws it to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne collects the ball by moving forward and whips the bails off by running towards the stumps. Both the batters are left stranded at the non-striker's end. Bangladesh lose their seventh wicket now.
Commentary.Howout: run out (Ryan Rickelton / Kyle Verreynne)

Commentary.Commentary: Another ball, full and outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives hard through cover. Dean Elgar there, puts in a dive and stops a certain boundary. The batters take a run. Mahmudul Hasan Joy moves into the 90s.

A length ball, around middle and leg. Yasir Ali tucks it around the corner and sets off for a run. Temba Bavuma at square leg, fails to grab the ball cleanly and Mahmudul Hasan Joy makes it safely to the striker's end.
A full ball, outside off. Yasir Ali pushes it towards cover.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Short and wide, outside off. Yasir Ali cuts it through the point region and collects a boundary.
FOUR! Top shot! Fuller in length, outside off. Yasir Ali drives it through the mid off region and bags a boundary. Excellent timing on that one!
A full ball, outside off. Yasir Ali drives it back to the bowler.
This is full and around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it out.
Play and a miss! A short ball, well outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy throws his bat at it but he fails to make any connection.
Back of a length, well outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it to the off side.
Short of a length, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out watchfully.
Olivier strays on the pads. Yasir Ali clips it towards the fine leg fielder for a run.
Edged but safe! Good-length ball, just outside off. Yasir Ali prods and looks to defend with soft hands. It takes the outside edge and runs past the gully fielder for a couple of runs.
On a length, around middle and leg. Yasir Ali tucks it past the mid-wicket fielder and takes a run.
On a length, around off. Yasir Ali hangs back and blocks it.
Short of a length, around off. Yasir Ali keeps it out, off the back foot.
A length ball, jagging back in from off. Yasir Ali gets forward and defends it towards mid on.
On a length and outside off. Yasir Ali lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, around leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy tickles it to fine leg for a single.
A length ball, outside off. Ali looks to chase it but misses.
Touch short, outside off. It nips in off the deck. Yasir Ali gets cramped for room here, but does enough to block it out.
Good length, wide outside off. Ali leaves it alone.
A length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Ali tries to defend inside the line but gets beaten, as the ball zips past the outside edge.
Full length, on the pads, Ali flicks it to deep mid-wicket. The batters take two runs. 200 comes up for Bangladesh!
Full length, outside off. Ali defends it out to cover.
Fuller, on the pads. Ali clips it to deep square leg for one.
Full length, outside off. Yasir Ali lunges and shoulders his arms at it.
Back of a length, outside off. Ali gets on top of it and cuts it hard through backward point. The batters take two before the fielder cuts it out.
A slower bouncer, down leg. Ali leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller, angled into off. Ali tucks it to short mid on.
Short ball, on top of off. Yasir Ali hangs back and blocks it to point.
Back of a length, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it to point.
Length ball, on the pads. Ali clips it to deep square leg for one.
Fuller, on off. Ali blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off, shaping away. Ali shoulders his arms at it.
Full length, on fifth stump. Ali defends it to cover on the front foot.
A sharp bouncer, on off. Ali sways away from the line of the delivery and leaves it alone.
Fuller, on the off stump. Joy gets his blade down just in time to defend it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Powerful stroke! Mahmudul Hasan Joy is on a roll. Lizaad Williams continues to bowl short, wide outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy rides the bounce really well and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Shorter again, outside off. Joy cuts it straight to point.
Back of a length, outside off. Joy guides it through backward point for two more runs.
Fuller, angled down leg. Ali flicks it to deep square leg for one more.
Full length, on the stumps. Joy stays back, closes the face and tucks it to mid-wicket for a quick single. He moves to 82.
Full length, on off. Ali punches it to mid on with soft hands.
The new ball is angled full and into the pads. Ali clears his front leg and tucks it to mid-wicket. Unable to thread it through the gap this time.
Fuller, on the pads. Ali clips it to deep square leg for a brace. He gets off the mark.
Full length, on the pads. Joy flicks it through square leg for a single.
Full length, yet again, wider than the previous delivery. Kyle Verreynne has to move a long way to his right to gather the ball. No shot offered.
Full length, wide outside off, it moves away off the deck. Mahmudul Hasan Joy slashes at it but misses.
The second new ball is available now. Will Dean Elgar opt for the same? No, he doesn't.
Pitches it up, just outside off. Yasir Ali prods and defends it solidly.
A short ball, angling down leg. Yasir Ali ducks underneath.
Back of a length, outside off. Yasir Ali shoulders his arms to this one.
On a length, around middle. Yasir Ali keeps it out.
Yasir Ali comes in at number 8.

OUT! BOWLED! Straight through the gate! That is a pearler from Lizaad Williams to get his second wicket of the innings! He strikes straightaway after Lunch break and this is a much-needed breakthrough for South Africa. Good-length delivery, jagging back in from the fifth stump channel. Das stays back to block but he misses. The ball brushes off his pad and cannons onto the stumps. Just the kind of start South Africa would have wished for after the break.
Commentary.Howout: b Lizaad Williams

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, outside off. Liton Das leaves it alone.

We are back for the second session on Day 3. South Africa players stride out to the middle. Followed by Liton Das and Mahmudul Hasan Joy who walk out to resume their batting. Lizaad Williams to start with the ball.
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

Mahmudul Hasan Joy desperately needed an ally after witnessing several dismissals from one end on Day 2 and he found one in Liton Das. Das could’ve perished on a timid score but Dean Elgar did not let that happen. Both the batters started aggressively against the spin twins and took them to the cleaners. Later, with some rub of green by their side, the Bangladesh batters managed to remain unscathed till Lunch on Day 3. South would be disappointed with their outing in the field. They will need to up their standards when they return to the field. Also, with the new ball in contention, the seamers will be itching to make a statement. Will they be able to repeat the feat of their spinners? To find out, do join us 1610 IST (1040 GMT). An enthralling session awaits.

The session could’ve belonged to South Africa, only if Dean Elgar hadn’t dropped a dolly at first slip when Liton Das was on 16. Nonetheless, Bangladesh would be really happy to have not lost any more wickets after the night watchman, Taskin Ahmed perished early on. The visiting side racked up 85 runs in 30 overs with the loss of just one wicket in the morning session on the moving day.
This is darted on the pads. Liton Das clips it behind square on the leg side for a single. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
TURN AND BOUNCE! This one drifts in from off and then turns away sharply. Liton Das looks to defend at first but does well to sway away from the line of the ball in the end.
Tossed up delivery, around off. Liton Das defends it off the front foot.
Slower through the air, on a length, around middle. Liton Das sits back and wrists it to mid-wicket.
Floated, full and around off. Liton Das keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Liton Das pushes it back to the bowler, off the back foot.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy leans and dabs it onto the deck.
On a length, around middle and leg. Liton Das glances it through fine leg and rotates the strike.
Floated, full and outside off. Das dead-bats it.
Flatter and quicker, turning in from middle. Liton Das tucks it to square leg.
Around off, blocked out.
Full and around middle. Das drags it to long on for a run. Joy moves to 80. This is now the highest score by a Bangladeshi player against South Africa in Test cricket.
Floated, around off. Liton Das blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Joy rocks back and cuts it past the point fielder for a single.
Nicely tossed up, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it out.
Quicker and fuller, on the stumps. Joy goes deep inside his crease and blocks it out.
Fuller, on leg. Joy goes back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Angled into the pads, blocked to short leg.

An appeal for caught at short leg but the umpire says no! South Africa have opted for a review! This is tossed up, around off and turning in sharply. Das prods to block but he misses and gets hit on his pad. The ball lobs up towards the short leg fielder who grabs it and South Africa appeal. The umpire is unmoved. The UltraEdge shows that there was clear daylight when the ball passed the bat. The on-field decision remains. The Proteas lose a review.
On a length, around off. Liton Das defends it off the front foot.
DROPPED! A length ball, around leg. Liton Das tickles it straight to the leg slip fielder. Wiaan Mulder there gets low to his left but puts it down.
Nicely tossed up, on off. Liton Das blocks it.
FOUR! Good use of the feet! Tossed up, around middle. Liton Das skips down the track and whacks it through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
This is darted on the pads. Liton Das misses his nudge on the leg side and gets hit on his pad.
Around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it.

FOUR! WHACKED! Another ball that is short and outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy rocks back and slashes hard through the cover region for another boundary. This is now the highest score by a Bangladeshi opening batter against South Africa in Tests.
Floated, on a length, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Short and outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy sits back in his crease and cuts it behind square on the off side for a boundary. Top shot. He picked the length so early!
Full and around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it solidly.
On a length, around middle. Liton Das blocks it with ease towards mid-wicket and takes a run.
This lands on a length, outside off and turns in late. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets an inside edge onto his pad as he looks to keep it out.
Slightly short and around middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets low, rocks back and pulls it towards the square leg fielder.
Tosses it up, around middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy lunges forward and dead-bats it.
On a length, around middle. Joy defends it.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy skips down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Liton Das hangs back and tucks it around the corner for a run.
A loopy ball, full and around middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy plunges forward and blocks it.
Floated, on a length, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone.
Cut away! Flatter and quicker, outside off. Liton Das hangs back and cuts it past the point fielder. The batters take three runs.
Tossed up, on off. Liton Das defends it off the front foot.
Around off. Blocked out.
Turn and bounce! Floated, on a length, around off and turning away sharply. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets squared up as he tries to defend it. It goes off the outside edge past the slip fielder for a run.
Tossed up delivery, around off. Liton Das defends it off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up, around middle. Liton Das flicks it towards square leg.
This is darted on the pads. Liton Das hangs back and tucks it around the corner.
Slightly short and around off. Liton Das rocks back and dabs it onto the deck.
Flighted delivery, around middle. Liton Das gets forward and keeps it out.
Das skips down the track and works it to mid-wicket.
Floated, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it.
Around middle. Liton Das clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Inside edge saves Liton Das this time! Tossed up delivery, around off. Liton Das prods to block but it goes off the inside edge and onto the pads.
On middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Floated, full and around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out.
Around off, blocked out.

Simon Harmer strikes on Day 3! But the celebration has to wait as Liton Das takes the review for caught behind. He challenges the umpire's decision here. It is loopy ball, angled down leg. Liton Das tries to flick it away but might've got the thinnest of inside edge. Simon Harmer appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Liton Das takes no time to opt for the review. The UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. It confirms that the ball comes off the thigh pad instead. The on-field decision has to be overturned. Thw bowlers need to toil harder to break this stand.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Liton Das smothers it to short leg.
Tossed up, on the pads. Joy clips it to mid-wicket for an easy single.
Full length, wide outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it through covers for a brace.
Full, on off, Joy defends it out watchfully.
Outside off, blocked back to the bowler.
Floated, full and around off. It grips and turns away sharply. It beats Das all ends up, as he tries to defend on the front foot.
Fuller, on leg. Das clips it to short leg on a bounce.
Angled into the pads, Das tucks it to short leg.
Fuller, on middle, blocked back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Floated, full and outside off. It grips and turns away a touch. Liton Das presses forward but fails to block it out. Gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full, on middle and leg. Das blocks it to short leg.
Full, outside off, Joy defends on his front foot.
Fuller, on middle, turning down leg. Joy clips it to the leg side.
On off, defended out solidly.
TWO LEG BYES! Loopy ball, around off. It grips and turns away down the leg side. The batters collect two leg byes, as it races down to fine leg off the pads.
Full, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy pushes it to mid off.
Quicker, fuller and down leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy goes back and takes a blow on his pad. Down the leg side though.
Fuller, on off. Das remains solid in his defense.
On off, blocked out.

Loopy ball, full and on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets low and goes for the sweep. It flies off the top edge and goes over square leg. Lizaad Williams runs backward but is unable to reach in time. The batters take a single.
Fuller, on off. Joy blocks it back to the bowler.
LEG BYE! Tossed up, on the pads. Das fails to flick it. The ball goes to square leg off the pads. The batters cross for a leg bye.

What a peach of a delivery. The South African players look excited. They take the review for caught behind. It is a flighted delivery, on off. The ball grips and turns away. Liton Das presses forward, tries to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge. Keshav Maharaj puts in a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. Although the sound that the players must've heard, was of Das' bat hitting his boot.
On off, blocked out solidly.

DROPPED! A tough chance though. It is fuller, on middle and leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy presses forward and tries to defend it out. The ball takes the outside edge and goes to the right of short leg. The fielders initial movement was to his left which takes him away from the ball.
Looped up, outside off, it grips and turns in. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it solidly.
Fuller, on leg. Joy defends it to short leg.
Full, on the stumps. Joy comes down the track and hits it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on the pads. Das clips it to square leg for a single.
Slower through the air, full and around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
A loopy ball, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy stretches forward and defends.
Floated, on a length, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy lunges forward and blocks it.
This is flatter and quicker, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy rocks back and works it to the backward point fielder.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out.
Full and outside off. Liton Das drives it wide of the long off fielder for a single.
Top delivery! Harmer tosses it up, around off and turning in sharply. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to defend but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Floated, on middle. Liton Das looks to heave it across the line but it goes off the inner half of the blade towards square leg for a run.

FOUR! Nicely timed! Slightly shorter in length, flatter and around middle. Das rocks back and just whips it through the mid-wicket region. The ball races away to the fence. Excellent timing on that one!
Tosses it up, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy skips down the track and eases it to long on for a single.
This is darted on the pads. Liton Das works it past the short leg fielder for a run.
Tossed up, outside off. Liton Das gets forward and wrists it to mid-wicket.

DRINKS! Whoa! That was some aggressive batting display by both the Bangladesh batters. They are fighting real hard to take their side to safer shores. South Africa need to rethink on their bowling combination. The attack of the spin twins is not able to cause any trouble like they did on Day 2. Will Dean Elgar stick with the same approach post Drinks? We shall find out soon. Stay tuned for an intriguing passage of play.
Floats it up, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out.
Tosses it up, outside off. Liton Das prods and defends it towards the point region. The batters cross ends.
FOUR! Nicely done! Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Liton Das hangs back and just guides it through the third man region for a boundary. Runs have suddenly started to flow for Bangladesh!
A loopy ball, around off. Liton Das leans and defends it towards the silly point fielder.
Floated, full and on off. Liton Das defends it off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Liton Das gets forward and keeps it out.
Around off. Blocked out.

SIX! BOOM! This is some batting from Mahmudul Hasan Joy! Good intent shown by the tourists on Day 3! This is tossed up, on middle. Joy skips down the track and lofts it way over long on for a maximum.
Harmer comes over the wicket now. He serves it on a length, around middle and turning in late. Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays back and tucks it to square leg.
Tossed up, on off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drives it back to the bowler.
Around off. Blocked out.
FOUR! BANG! Tossed up, in the slot, on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy clears his front leg and whacks it past the diving fielder at mid on for a boundary.
In the air...but safe! Flighted delivery, full and on off. Das looks to play it across the line. It goes off the leading edge, just past the short cover fielder. A maiden from Keshav Maharaj!
Slower through the air, on a length, around middle. Liton Das hangs back and dabs it onto the deck.
Tossed up delivery, around off. Liton Das blocks it.
Flatter and quicker, full, around off. Liton Das dead-bats it.
Floated, full and around middle. Liton Das gets forward and blocks it.
Tossed up, around off. Liton Das keeps it out.
Full, on middle and leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy prods and defends it to the right of the bowler.
Touch short, on the pads. Joy pulls it to square leg.
Looped up, around off, defended out.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated, full and on off. Joy flicks it towards mid on. Dean Elgar misfields and the batters take a brace.

FOUR! Mahmudul Hasan Joy welcomes Harmer into the attack in a fine manner. Tossed up, full and outside off. Joy slaps it down the ground and bags a boundary at long off. He gets to his second Test fifty. The pavilion rises to applause this knock.
Spin from both ends now. Simon Harmer comes to bowl.
Fuller, on off. Das lunges and blocks it forward.
Darted on the pads, Joy nudges it to square leg for a single this time.
Floated, full and on off. Joy defends it solidly on the front foot.
Tossed up, full, on middle and leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy defends it to the leg side off the inner half.
Fuller, on the pads, Joy flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full, on off, Joy eases it to mid on.
Finally, Dean Elgar brings on a spinner. Keshav Maharaj comes into the attack.
Fuller, on the pads. Das clips it to mid-wicket.
Full length, on fourth stump. Liton Das pushes it gently back to the bowler.
Length, on off, blocked to cover.
Length ball, on the pads. Das clips it to mid-wicket. The fielder does well to not let it race away.
Full length, on off. Das blocks it back to the bowler.

EDGED AND DROPPED! A regulation catch at slips and it is the skipper, Dean Elgar who fails to pouch it. A length ball, outside off, shaping away a touch. Liton Das goes fishing away from his body. The ball takes the thick outside edge and goes towards first slip. Dean Elgar though misses out on a dolly.
Length, on the pads. Liton Das clips it through mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, outside off. Das punches it through covers for a brace.

FOUR! Edgy! A short ball, on the bodyline. Liton Das swivels and heaves across the line. The ball flies off the top-edge, beats the diving effort of Kyle Verreynne behind the sticks and races over the ropes at fine leg.
Fuller, on the off stump. Das blocks it back to the bowler.
Length ball, outside off. Das taps it to cover.
Full length, on off, blocked out solidly.
Bangs it short, around leg. Joy leaves it alone for the keeper.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line. It climbs onto the batter. Joy steers it straight to gully.
NO BALL! A sharp bouncer, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy leaves it alone. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
Length ball, on off. Joy defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy sways away from the line of the delivery.
Full length, on off, blocked out.
Lenght ball, outside off. Joy taps it to cover.
Good-length delivery, nipping back in slightly from outside off. Das lets it sail through to the keeper. Another maiden over from Olivier!
Fuller in length, around the fourth stump channel. Liton Das defends it off the front foot.
Pitches it up this time, outside off. Das does not bother playing at it.
On a length, around off. Das blocks it to the off side.
Good-length delivery, around off. Liton Das covers his off pole and keeps it out.
A length ball, jagging back in from outside off and staying a touch low. Das shoulders his arms to this one.
Back of a length, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets behind the line of the delivery and blocks it solidly.
Another ball that is full and around middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy gets forward and works it to mid on.
A full ball, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy leans and drives it to the mid on fielder.
Shorter in length, around middle. Liton Das swivels and pulls it without much timing towards fine leg for a run.
Back of a length, angling in from middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy stays back and tickles it to fine leg for a single.
Fuller in length, just outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to drive without any feet movement. He gets an inside edge onto his pad.
This is a full ball, angling in from off. Das gets forward and pushes it to mid off, off the inner half of the bat.
On a length, around off and shaping away late. Liton Das looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
FOUR! WHACKED! Das is making his intentions quite clear here! A length ball, outside off. Das hangs back and punches it through the cover-point region for a cracking boundary.
A wayward ball, well outside off. Das lets it through to the keeper.
FOUR! Pulled away! A short ball, around off. Das stands tall and pulls it in front of square and gets off the mark in some style. A shot of authority from Das!
A length ball, around leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy tucks it behind square on the leg side and takes a single.
Back of a length, outside off. Liton Das gets forward and defends it out.
No ball! A full ball, outside off. Liton Das prods and pushes it to mid off. The umpire calls it a no ball as Williams oversteps.

That nipped back in sharply! This delivery jags back in from off. Some extra bounce on offer for Williams. Liton Das sits back to block but he misses and gets hit high on his body. He seems to be in pain.
Shorter in length, angling in from outside off. Liton Das lets it be.
A length ball, outside off. Liton Das leaves it alone.
On a length, around off. Liton Das keeps it out.
Liton Das is the new batter in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Lizaad Williams gets his first wicket in Test cricket and he is delighted! Bangladesh's night watchman departs and this is a good start for South Africa! Back of a length, angling across the batter from outside off. Taskin Ahmed looks to push it through the off side, away from his body. He only manages a thick outside edge which goes straight to Wiaan Mulder at gully. Mulder looks to grab it with hard hands, the ball pops out of his hands, to his right and he recovers well to complete a juggling catch.
Commentary.Howout: c Wiaan Mulder b Lizaad Williams

Commentary.Commentary: Play and a miss! Back of a length, well outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy sits back and looks to push it through the off side but he fails to get any bat on it. Olivier starts with a maiden over!
This one comes in late from outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of the bat towards backward point.

Temba Bavuma is up for a quick chat. He says that it was disappointing to not get a big hundred for his side. Adds that they had a lot of positives and he enjoyed batting against the seamers. Tells that they had a good Day 2 and they'll now look to go well on Day 3 as well. Mentions that he is very confident about his batting and it is going well at the moment for him. Says that they want to start well with the ball and make use of the overcast conditions.

South Africa have posted a good first innings total and their spinners have also done a terrific job with the ball to ensure that the Proteas stay ahead in this Test. They will now look to pick the remaining wickets sooner rather than later and get healthy first innings lead. Who will take the first session of Day 3? Stay tuned as we shall find that soon.

Hello and a very warm welcome to Day 3 of the first Test between Bangladesh and South Africa. The Test has moved at a rapid pace and it is South Africa who are clearly in the driving seat, heading into the moving day. Bangladesh have a tough task in front of them and they will need to bat out of their skins, if they are to stay alive in the contest.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

Right then. That’s it from the coverage of Day 2. This game has moved at a really good pace as we head into Day 3. Bangladesh seems to be in a lot of trouble as they still trail by 269 runs with just six wickets in hand. South African spinners have done the trick for them, especially Simon Harmer. The seamers are yet to play their part for South Africa. They will be eager to make a statement with the ball, come Day 3. The action resumes on Saturday at 1.30 pm IST (8 am GMT). But as you all know, you can join us early for the build-up. Cheers!

Earlier in the day, it was the tail of South Africa that wagged and frustrated Bangladesh after Temba Bavuma fell just 7 runs short of his second Test hundred. The tourists did manage to pull things back in their favour with the second new ball but they failed to capitalize on the momentum that they had and leaked 69 runs in search of the last two wickets.

Simon Harmer has ensured that South Africa end the Day 2 on a high. He kept things really tight in the middle, along with Keshav Maharaj and the pair bowled with great control. It was Harmer who grabbed four crucial wickets and South Africa find themselves in a really good position now. For Bangladesh, Najmul Hossain Shanto and Mahmudul Hasan Joy batted really well for a long period of time but they failed to bat through the session and it was Shanto who got out to an unplayable delivery. That opened the floodgates for the Proteas and they picked wickets in quick succession. Mahmudul Hasan Joy has held one end nicely for Bangladesh and they would hope that he bats deep and takes them to safer shores.

Well, if things were even-steven at the end of Day 1, Day 2 has certainly belonged to South Africa. They surely have the upper hand heading into Day 3. Surprisingly, it has been South Africa's spinners that have dominated proceedings, as their pacers were forced to stay away due to the fading light. Bangladesh would be disappointed at the end of the day's play as they looked quite comfortable at one point when Mahmudul Hasan Joy and Najmul Hossain Shanto were grinding it out in the middle. They now have their task cut out going into Day 3.

Bangladesh head into the break with a huge blow at the stroke of Tea. The new ball hasn’t been much effective for the Proteas even with the cloud cover across the venue. The seaming pair of Olivier and Williams started from each end but could not trouble the batters at all. Later, Simon Harmer was brought into the attack to work some magic, and boy, he succeeded in drawing the first blood. Bangladesh still have ample batting to come. Although, they have their task cut out. South Africa will be eager to come out and take a couple of more wickets before Stumps on Day 2. Will they be able to do so? We shall find out soon. Join us at 1845 IST (1315 GMT) for an intriguing final session of Day 2.

South Africa take the momentum along with them at the Tea break. Bangladesh could not end this session well. The afternoon session did not start well for them either, as their bowlers leaked aplenty while hunting down the last two wickets and allowed South Africa to get over the 350-run mark. South Africa seem to be in a comfortable position now.

South Africa have set a target of 274 runs for Bangladesh. The hosts came into bat with a lead of 69 runs, although they did not get enough time at the crease due to early stumps on Day 3. The hosts started positively in the morning session on Day 4 by losing only a single wicket of Sarel Erwee. Their worse nightmare was yet to come, as Bangladesh roared back in the afternoon session. The visitors took 4 wickets in that session and did manage to put a lid over the run rate as well. Later, only Ryan Rickelton was the stand out batter for South Africa, who did manage to bat till the end but could not apply the same pressure with the tail-enders. South Africa lost their last three wickets in 8 deliveries and that would hurt them a lot. Bangladesh bowlers turned on the heat with the ball since the afternoon session. It was a combination of pace and spin attack that did the trick for them. Mehidy Hasan was the pick of the bowlers with three wickets. Ebadot Hossain also enjoyed his time out with the ball, as he grabbed three wicket as well. The onus is now on the Bangladeshi batters. They have about an hour and a whole day's play in hand to chase the target. Will they be able to convert it into a win? Do join us in a short while for the chase.

This afternoon session has truly belonged to one team and that is the visiting side. While one end worked with pace, the other one was single-handedly managed by Mehidy Hasan. The bowlers worked in tandem, with the fielders being much more attentive on the field. This certainly changed the scenario for Bangladesh. South Africa only managed to score 52 runs in 28 overs. The Bangladeshi bowlers picked up four wickets in this session, out of which two belonged to Hasan, while Taskin Ahmed and Ebadot Hossain picked a wicket each. The South African batters were not able to score as freely as they did in the morning session and that might hurt them a lot. It could’ve gotten worse for the home side but with some rub of green they managed to not lose any more wickets till Tea. South Africa lead by 226 runs now. They would look to get near the 300-run mark before speculating any declaration for their side. In whose favor will the game shift towards in the final session of Day 4? To find out, join us at 1900 IST (1330 GMT).

The Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing the wickets. The umpire is forced to overturn his original decision. Kyle Verreynne survives. This is the eighth decision that has been overturned in this Test match so far.
Fuller, outside off. Ryan Rickelton pushes it to mid off for a single.
Around off, Ryan Rickelton blocks it out.

Good-length ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and pushes it towards cover, off the back foot.
Short of a length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton punches it past the fielder at cover and rotates the strike.
BEATEN! This is a length ball, outside off and staying a tad low. Ryan looks to push it through the off side, off the back foot but the ball sneaks past his blade.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short of a length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton hangs back and caresses it through the point region to bag a boundary.
Ahmed drags his length back a bit, just outside off. Ryan Rickelton stands tall and punches it to mid off.
Ahmed goes 'round the wicket and serves a good-length ball, around off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out.
This one spins in sharply from outside off. Kyle Verreynne sits back in his crease and defends it out watchfully. Another maiden over from Mehidy Hasan!
Another ball, quicker and on middle. Kyle Verreynne manages to dab it onto the deck.
This is a flatter ball, turning in sharply from outside off. Kyle Verreynne gets cramped for room as he looks to cut that one.
Flatter ball, turning in from middle. Kyle Verreynne rocks back and tickles it to short fine leg.
Nicely tossed up, on middle. Kyle Verreynne blocks it off the front foot.
Floated, full and on middle. Kyle Verreynne wrists it to mid-wicket.
A full ball, around off. Ryan Rickelton prods and pushes it to mid on. 6 runs off the over!
Back of a length, around middle. Ryan Rickelton tucks it to square leg, off the back foot.
FOUR! SMASHED! Short and wide, outside off. Ryan stays back, throws his bat it. It goes off the outer half of the bat and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Hossain bowls it full, around off. Ryan defends it off the front foot.
A short ball, around off. Ryan Rickelton pulls it along the ground, in front of square on the leg side for a brace.
Short of a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton stays back and dabs it onto the deck.
This is darted on the pads. Ryan Rickelton tucks it around the corner for a run.
A quicker ball, on a length and going on with the angle. Ryan manages to defend it off the back foot.
This is a flatter ball, on middle. Ryan Rickelton hangs back and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, around off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out.
Flatter and around off. Ryan Rickelton rocks back and punches it to cover.
A full ball, around off. Kyle digs it out to the off side for a single.

DRINKS! South Africa lead by 201 runs at the moment. But Bangladesh has made inroads in this game with some crucial wickets. With two new batters at the crease, Bangladesh will be hoping to end things early and come back out to chase before Stumps. How will the fifth-wicket stand fare for the Proteas? Stick around to find out.
Full and outside off. Ryan Rickelton drives it to the fielder at mid off.
Back of a length, outside off. Ryan pushes it to the off side.
On a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton blocks it with ease.
A bumper, angling down leg. Ryan Rickelton ducks underneath. The umpire calls it wide for height.
Another ball, back of a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton defends it to the off side.
Good-length delivery, just outside off. Ryan Rickelton dabs it onto the deck.
A full ball, angling in from outside off. Ryan Rickelton leaves it alone.
Fuller, around off. Kyle Verreynne tries to defend it on the front foot. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
On off, clipped to mid on.
Flighted, full and on leg. Kyle Verreynne fails to defend it out. The ball lobs to short leg off the pads.
Full, outside off. Ryan Rickelton drives it to mid off. The fielder there misfields and the batters take a single. South Africa now lead by 200 runs!
This is full, on middle. Ryan Rickelton flicks it to short leg.
Fuller, outside off. Ryan Rickelton prods and tries to defend it to silly point. But it lands short of the fielder there.
FOUR! Kyle Verreynne gets off the mark with a boundary. A length ball, angled down leg. Kyle Verreynne tickles it down to fine leg for a boundary. The lead moves to 199.

OUT! CAUGHT! OH MY GOD! Yasir Ali, you beauty! In the morning session, Ali did drop a catch at slips. But this chance is even tougher and he grabs it with a single hand. Temba Bavuma cannot do anything about it other than walking back to the dressing room. Coming to the delivery - it is a length ball, around off, shaping away off the deck. Temba Bavuma hangs his blade away from his body. The ball takes the outside edge, goes to the left of first slip. Yasir Ali dives to that side and takes a stunning one-handed catch. Bangladesh are back in the game now.
Commentary.Howout: c Yasir Ali b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary.Commentary: On a length, outside off, nips in a touch late. Temba Bavuma steps across and shoulders his arms at it.
Full length, on the stumps. Bavuma defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma defends it to the off side.
Full, on leg. Ryan Rickelton clips it to short fine leg.
Full, on the off stump. Ryan Rickelton prods and blocks it into the deck.
Ryan Rickelton walks in at number 5.

OUT! CAUGHT! Elation for Bangladesh. They pick up the third wicket of the innings. Mehidy Hasan gets his first wicket of the innings. He gets rid of a set batter in Keegan Petersen. It is fuller, quicker and on the pads. Keegan Petersen clips it straight to short leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy stationed there, stays low and grabs the ball sharply. Keegan Petersen trudges back off the field.
Commentary.Howout: c Mahmudul Hasan Joy b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary.Commentary: Touch fuller, on leg. Bavuma eases it down to long on for a single.
Full, on off. Bavuma defends it to short leg yet again.
Floated and full, on off. Bavuma tucks it to short leg.
Length ball, on the pads. Temba Bavuma flicks it to mid-wicket for a quick single. He will retain the strike.
Full length, outside off. Bavuma drives it to cover.
Good length, in the corridor of uncertainty. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller, on off. Temba Bavuma blocks it to the leg side.
Landing on a length, on top of off. Temba Bavuma defends it out watchfully.
Length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma lets it be.
Tossed up, full and on off. Keegan Petersen comes down the track and pats it back to the bowler. The lead is 193 now.
Quicker and fuller, on the pads. Keegan Petersen flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter, on leg. Keegan Petersen blocks it to short leg.
On off, clipped to mid on.
Fuller, on off. Keegan Petersen pushes it to the right of the bowler.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is tossed up, full and outside off. Keegan Petersen stride forward and drives it through covers for an exceptional boundary.
Pitched up, around off. Temba Bavuma keeps it out.

Edged but it falls short of the fielder! A length ball, just outside off. Bavuma looks to block it off the front foot. It takes the outside edge and goes towards the slip fielder, on the bounce. It didn't carry to the fielder there as Bavuma played it with soft hands.
Back of a length, just outside off. Keegan Petersen defends it to the off side and takes a run.
On a length, around off. Kept out.

A big mix-up but no harm done! Although, had that been another direct hit from Mehidy Hasan, it was curtains for Keegan Petersen! A length ball, around off. KP taps it to cover and looks for a run. Temba Bavuma sends him back. Mehidy Hasan misses his shy at the striker's end and KP survives.
On a length, around middle. Keegan Petersen defends it towards mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter in length, outside off. Temba Bavuma mistimes his cut shot towards the mid off fielder.
Edged but safe! Flatter and quicker, going on with the angle from just outside off. Temba Bavuma sits back to block but it goes off the thick outside edge, past the slip fielder for a brace.
Flatter and around middle. Temba Bavuma defends it to the leg side.
Tosses it up, outside off. Bavuma prods but keeps his bat away from the line of the ball.
This is darted on the pads. Keegan Petersen tucks it around the corner and settles for a single.
Floated, outside off. Keegan Petersen skips down the track and keeps it out.
Short of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma cuts it nicely but fails to find the gap. He hits it straight to the backward point fielder. A wicket-maiden from Taskin Ahmed!
Pitches it up, outside off. Bavuma drives but Mehidy Hasan at extra cover dives to his left and stops it.
Around off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Temba Bavuma is the new man in.

A loud shout for LBW but the umpire is unmoved! Bangladesh though have sent it upstairs. Was there any bat involved in it? No, says the UltraEdge! The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the ball would have crashed into the middle stump. It is three reds. Lovely delivery from Taskin! This was a length ball, nipping back in just that little bit from off. Elgar sits back and tries to keep it out. He misses as the ball beats the inside edge of his bat. Elgar is pinged on the pads and Taskin Ahmed appeals. Bangladesh opt for a review as the on-field umpire doesn't agree. Three reds on the Ball Tracker and it is pumb in front. The on-field decision is overturned! Massive wicket for Bangladesh!
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Taskin Ahmed

Play and a miss! Back of a length, well outside off. Elgar hangs back and throws his bat at it. The ball zips past his blade.
Floated, full and on off. Keegan Petersen comes down the track and drills it back to the bowler.
Keegan Petersen skips down the track and drives it to mid on.
Another ball, flatter and quicker, on a length, and spinning in from middle. Keegan Petersen works it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter ball, turning in from middle. Keegan Petersen rocks back and tucks it to square leg.
Full and on off. Keegan Petersen pushes it back to the bowler.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire says no! Tossed up, outside off. Keegan Petersen kneels and looks to reverse-sweep but he misses and gets hit on his pad. The impact might have been outside off.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Dean Elgar leans and pushes it to cover.
Good-length delivery, around off. Elgar gets behind the line of the ball and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A bit of inswing for Taskin! A length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Keegan Petersen looks to drive but it goes off the outer half towards deep cover for a run.

Short of a length, around off. Dean Elgar blocks it off the back foot.
On a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen taps it past the backward point fielder and takes a run.

Elgar flicks a full delivery to mid-wicket for one.
Around off, pushed to cover.
Short, on off. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Who will start from the other end? Mehidy Hasan it is.
It is length ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen shoulders his arms at it.
Full length, just outside off. Keegan Petersen blocks it out watchfully.
Outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone for the keeper.
A length ball, on off. Keegan Petersen defends it out solidly.
